us-branch-database-however-our-local-setup-now-spli',5,NULL,1,'2016-08-18 15:44:27','2016-08-18 15:44:30','2016-08-18 15:44:30'),(38,7,'Manual Client Advanced Exports','How to download and transfer client advanced exports manually to clients.','<h3>Exports Ran Correctly - Data On Live Server</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Download the export data&nbsp;from the live server using SFTP\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>On ivnode14, this can be found in:&nbsp;/mnt/nfs_vnode20_docs/docs0/IAPTus_Documents/all_docs/documentService134/exports</li>\r\n		<li>On ivnode7, this can be found in:&nbsp;/mnt/iaptus_docs/IAPTus_Documents/all_docs/documentServiceZZZ/exports, where ZZZ is their service ID</li>\r\n		<li>We keep three days worth of data, so pick the one for the day you need</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Use Teamviewer 10</strong>&nbsp;in file transfer mode to transfer the data to the client\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>You will need to telephone the client to get their Teamviewer credentials</li>\r\n		<li>Note, this&nbsp;<strong>must</strong>&nbsp;be Teamviewer 10, as per the ISMS documents</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Exports Did Not Run</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Put the master branch on a test site and deploy, using the services database.</li>\r\n	<li>Go into the Control Panel on the front end, turn exports on</li>\r\n	<li>Make sure the folder html_live/documents/documentServiceZZZ/exports/ exists and has write permissions, where ZZZ is their service ID</li>\r\n	<li>Go to cron_live/cron-config.php and uncomment the lines for \"CronExports\"</li>\r\n	<li>Run the following command in the cron_live folder: \"php cron.php\"</li>\r\n	<li>Once the cron has run, comment the lines in cron-config.php again</li>\r\n	<li>Grab the data files and place them in the location detailed in the instructions above</li>\r\n	<li>If they can\'t download it from their own link, follow the steps above to transfer manually</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n','manual-client-advanced-exports',4,1,24,'2016-08-19 12:18:34','2016-09-22 13:15:15',NULL),(39,7,'Turn On SMS For A Service','How to get a service set up with SMS','<h1>SMS Setup</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>To enable SMS for a service, all it requires is a patch, though this patch will be different, depending on whether the service is CYP or Adult.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Common Patch</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The common part of the patch is as follows, do <strong>note </strong>that some of these variables may already exist in their database, so you need to check this before writing the patch.</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n# Set service ID and set global vars (note: some of these may already exist in the database so check first)\r\nSET @ser_id = 100; \r\n\r\nINSERT INTO `nh_global` (`var_name`, `var_value`, `var_type`, `ser_id`, `live`, `Notes`) \r\nSELECT \'smsDaysAdvance\', \'2\', NULL, @ser_id, 1, \'Max 26 days (less than the shortest month)\' FROM nh_service WHERE ser_id = @ser_id;\r\n\r\nINSERT INTO `nh_global` (`var_name`, `var_value`, `var_type`, `ser_id`, `live`, `Notes`) \r\nSELECT \'smsDaysAdvanceQueue\', \'3\', NULL, @ser_id, 1, NULL FROM nh_service WHERE ser_id = @ser_id;\r\n\r\nINSERT INTO `nh_global` (`var_name`, `var_value`, `var_type`, `ser_id`, `live`, `Notes`) \r\nSELECT \'smsMasterswitch\', \'1\', NULL, @ser_id, 1, \'\' FROM nh_service WHERE ser_id = @ser_id;\r\n\r\nINSERT INTO `nh_global` (`var_name`, `var_value`, `var_type`, `ser_id`, `live`, `Notes`) \r\nSELECT \'smsTime\', \'12\', NULL, @ser_id, 1, \'\' FROM nh_service WHERE ser_id = @ser_id;\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h2>Adult Service</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>If the service is an <strong>Adult Service </strong>then you need to add the following to the patch, to provide them with SMS templates that use Adult MDS values:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n# Insert some default templates that are disabled\r\nINSERT INTO `nh_sms_templates` (`sms_type`, `mds_refId`, `type`, `ser_id`, `message_template`, `live`) \r\nSELECT 3, 116, \'Face-to-face\', ser_id, \'You have a group appointment at [--------LOCATION--------] on [-------DATE--