ith &#39;sessions&#39; and &#39;episodes&#39;. Read about sessions <a href=\"#sessions\">here</a>.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Episodes</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In the iaptus system, episodes are synonymous with &#39;sessions&#39;. Read about sessions <a href=\"#sessions\">here</a>.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Referrals</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Referrals are also known as treatments and are stored in the <code>nh_treatment</code> table. As far as the system is concerned, &#39;referrals&#39; and &#39;treatments&#39; are synonomous and refer to a specific avenue of treatment that a patient receives. A patient may receive multiple avenues of treatment depending on their problem descriptor or stages of other treatments at the time. Sessions/episodes belong to specific referrals/treatments, and each referral/treatment belongs to a patient.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Sessions</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sessions are also known as &#39;episodes&#39; and &#39;clinical contacts&#39;, and are stored&nbsp;in the <code>nh_session</code> table. The word &#39;session&#39; describes any official contact that a patient has had with a therapist during the course of a <a href=\"#referrals\">treatment or referral</a>. This could be face to face in a therapist&#39;s office, over the phone, in group sessions and more - there are many different types of session&nbsp;a patient can participate in. Each session belongs to one iaptus <a href=\"#referrals\">referral</a>.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Treatments</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>In the iaptus system, treatments are synonymous with &#39;referrals&#39;. Read about referrals <a href=\"#referrals\">here</a>.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,26,'2016-08-02 17:05:19','2016-08-03 08:58:01',NULL),(20,23,15,'Public Live Sites List','List of sites on public access servers','<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td colspan=\"6\">\r\n			<p><strong>maydenasvnode1</strong>: &nbsp;Generic Wordpress Host</p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\