 is the safest way of getting a bournmoth site to bracknell. This can be done at any time of the day as providing you do everything right there is very minimal risk.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please replace the in the below commands with the details below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SERVICE_DB_NAME</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Name of the DB you need to copy</li>\r\n	<li>e.g. IAPTus_IOW</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DB_USER_NAME</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your master DB user name</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PORT</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3306 for Set 4</li>\r\n	<li>3312 for Set 5</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ ssh iaptusvnode26</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ cd ~/</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysqldump -u -p -h 10.0.2.55 -P --add-drop-table --skip-lock-tables --skip-add-locks --compress --skip-triggers --ignore-table=.nh_stats_history --ignore-table=.nh_stats --ignore-table=.nh_user_activity_view --ignore-table=.nh_user_activity_edit &gt; .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysqldump -u -p -h 10.0.2.55 -P &nbsp;--add-drop-table --compress --no-data nh_stats --no-data nh_stats_history --no-data nh_user_activity_view --no-data nh_user_activity_edit &gt;&gt; .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysqldump IAPTus_Global -u -p -h 10.0.2.55 -P &nbsp;--add-drop-table --skip-lock-tables --skip-add-locks --compress --skip-triggers --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_gp_bak --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_gp_import --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_practice_bak --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_practice_import &gt; IAPTus_Global.sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysql -u -p -h 10.0.2.54 -P 3306 &lt; .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysql -u -p -h 10.0.2.54 -P 3306 &lt; IAPTus_Global.sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ rm .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ rm IAPTus_Global.sql</div>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-11 14:43:43','2016-08-11 14:43:43',NULL),(50,25,1,'Copying Data to Test Sites (Same Datacenter)','Instructions for how to copy a live database to a test site','<p>1.&nbsp;Find which data center the service is located by looking at the <a href=\"/p/mayden/servers/server-details\">&#39;Servers&#39;</a> page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. VPN into the relevant&nbsp;datacenter and&nbsp;SSH into the relevant&nbsp;server.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Get the size of the database by looking it up in HeidiSQL and double check with&nbsp;devOps that it is an appropriate size/time to copy it accross.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Navigate to:&nbsp;<code>/var/www/html/iaptus/tools</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Run the command which will copy the database you need to the test server:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>php copy_db_to_test.php</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5.&nbsp;Follow the prompts from the script to complete the process:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Enter admin level credentials for the source database when prompted.</li>\r\n	<li>Select the source database when prompted.</li>\r\n	<li>Select the destination when prompted</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Check live site <a href=\"testing-a3.iaptus.nhs.uk:8000\">testing-a3</a> is up and running:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Login with your service credentials:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>mayden.{initials}.{servicename}</li>\r\n		<li>password allocated to you by devOps</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-11 14:44:15',