s.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You can write helpers to handle common functionality sensors might need like connecting to all <a href=\"https://github.com/may-den/iaptus-sensors/blob/master/src/Databases/PdoConnectionIterator.php\">databases</a>.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Iaptus Sensors</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Create a new Metric or Check file for your sensor.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Take a look at existing sensors to see how they are written.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will need to add a query for your sensor using the $sensorQuery property.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will need to add a .json config file in the same directory as your sensor (take a look at other .json config files for reference)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will need to give your sensor a name using the $sensorName property.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Add your sensor to config/di-config.php file.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Postroom Sensor</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Create a new Metric or Check file for your sensor.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Take a look at existing sensors to see how they are written.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will need to add a query for your sensor using the $sensorQuery property.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will need to give your sensor a name using the $sensorName property.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will need to add a .json config file in the same directory as your sensor (take a look at other .json config files for reference)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Add your sensor to config/di-config.php file.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>How To Test</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Use TDD! Write tests as you go to make sure your sensor is behaving as you would expect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also copy changes into the sensor-manager version of your sensor repo in the vendor directory and run the sensor from your console.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Running Sensu</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><code>php SensorManager.php run Iaptus Users\\\\Metrics\\\\UniqueUserLoginsPerService</code></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Running Tests</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Run &lsquo;<code>composer test</code>&rsquo; from either the iaptus-sensors or postroom-sensors repo.</p>\r\n',1,10,'2016-08-11 15:02:22','2016-08-11 15:02:32',NULL),(56,26,4,'How To Sensu','An overview of how to create sensors and run them with Sensu.','<h3>First Things First</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Read the wikis for <a href=\"https://github.com/may-den/sensor-manager/wiki\">sensor-manager</a> and <a href=\"https://github.com/may-den/sensor-services/wiki\">sensor-services</a>. &nbsp;The sensor-manager allows you to run a sensor from the command line while the sensor-services repo contains interfaces and classes that must be implemented by your sensors. Also look at the sensu <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/document/d/1O7G4-pjmZ2bSiuj1CJV_4O-wOtt80D5MMIW36-DONp8/\">document</a> for conventions relating to checks and metrics.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>How To Make A Sensor</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Go to the sensor repo of the product that you&rsquo;re writing a sensor for e.g <a href=\"https://github.com/may-den/postroom-sensors\">postroom-sensors</a>. &nbsp;The <a href=\"https://github.com/may-den/iaptus-sensors/blob/master/README.md\">readme</a> should give you instructions on how to create a sensor.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Here is an example of a <a href=\"https://github.com/may-den/iaptus-sensors/blob/master/src/Sms/Metrics/SmsCount.php\">sensor</a> in iaptus-sensors.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You can write helpers to handle common functionality sensors might need like connecting to all <a href=\"https://github.com/may-den/iaptus-sensors/blob/master/src/Databases/PdoConnectionIterator.php\">databases</a>.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Postroom &amp; iaptus Sensors</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Create a new Metric or Check file for your sensor.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Take a look at existing sensors to see how they are written.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will need to add a query for your sensor using the $sensorQuery property.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will need to add a .json config file in the same directory as your sensor (take a look at other .json config files for reference)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>You will need to give your sensor a name using the $sensorName property.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Add your sensor to config/di-config.php file</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>How To Test</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Use TDD! Write tests as you go to make sure your sensor is behaving as you would expect.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can also copy changes into the sensor-manager version of your sensor repo in the vendor directory and run the sensor from your console.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Running Sensu</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><code>php SensorManager.php run Iaptus Users\\\\Metrics\\\\UniqueUserLoginsPerService</code></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Running Tests</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Run &lsquo;<code>composer test</code>&rsquo; from either the iaptus-sensors or postroom-sensors repo.</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-11 15:04:05','2016-08-11 15:04:05',NULL),(57,24,1,'Test Sites: Deploying ','Instructions on how to deploy a branch of code to a test site.','<p>Open the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1HO9zfbEycSBxlsYeKikhzh3N8jBJrkwTljcG4kxx3FA\">developer portal</a>&nbsp;spreadsheet and pick any&nbsp;testing server which is available,&nbsp;allocating it to yourself .</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>VPN into the appropriate data-center and&nbsp;SSH to the appropriate server:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><code>iaptusvnode26</code> for &#39;a&#39; testing sites</li>\r\n	<li><code>iaptusvnode7</code> for &#39;b&#39; testing sites</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Change directories to the live build script in the source code folder:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>cd /var/www/html/iaptustest-testing-a4/build/live</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Switch branches to the branch you need to check out:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>phing switch-testing</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Insert GitHub read-only password twice found in Mayden KeePass.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Run the command which deploys the branch you just checked out:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>phing deploy-local</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enter the database username/password of the data set that is currently on the test site.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Go to your testing site and ensure everything is up and running.</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-11 15:06:16','2016-08-11 15:06:16',NULL),(58,25,1,'Test Sites: Copying Databases (Same Datacenter)','Instructions for how to copy a live database to a test site','<p>1.&nbsp;Find which data center the service is located by looking at the <a href=\"/p/mayden/servers/server-details\">&#39;Servers&#39;</a> page.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. VPN into the relevant&nbsp;datacenter and&nbsp;SSH into the relevant&nbsp;server.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Get the size of the database by looking it up in HeidiSQL and double check with&nbsp;devOps that it is an appropriate size/time to copy it accross.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Navigate to:&nbsp;<code>/var/www/html/iaptus/tools</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Run the command which will copy the database you need to the test server:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>php copy_db_to_test.php</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5.&nbsp;Follow the prompts from the script to complete the process:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Enter admin level credentials for the source database when prompted.</li>\r\n	<li>Select the source database when prompted.</li>\r\n	<li>Select the destination when prompted</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>6. Check live site <a href=\"testing-a3.iaptus.nhs.uk:8000\">testing-a3</a> is up and running:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Login with your service credentials:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>mayden.{initials}.{servicename}</li>\r\n		<li>password allocated to you by devOps</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-11 15:07:03','2016-08-11 15:07:03',NULL),(59,30,1,'Test Sites: Copying Data (Bmth to Brck)','Instructions for how to copy a live database from Bournemouth to a test site on Bracknell','<h3 style=\"color:#aaa; font-style:italic\">Please make sure you read and understand all these commands before executing them. This is the safest way of getting a bournmoth site to bracknell. This can be done at any time of the day as providing you do everything right there is very minimal risk.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please replace the in the below commands with the details below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SERVICE_DB_NAME</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Name of the DB you need to copy</li>\r\n	<li>e.g. IAPTus_IOW</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DB_USER_NAME</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your master DB user name</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PORT</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3306 for Set 4</li>\r\n	<li>3312 for Set 5</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ ssh iaptusvnode26</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ cd ~/</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysqldump -u -p -h 10.0.2.55 -P --add-drop-table --skip-lock-tables --skip-add-locks --compress --skip-triggers --ignore-table=.nh_stats_history --ignore-table=.nh_stats --ignore-table=.nh_user_activity_view --ignore-table=.nh_user_activity_edit &gt; .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysqldump -u -p -h 10.0.2.55 -P &nbsp;--add-drop-table --compress --no-data nh_stats --no-data nh_stats_history --no-data nh_user_activity_view --no-data nh_user_activity_edit &gt;&gt; .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysqldump IAPTus_Global -u -p -h 10.0.2.55 -P &nbsp;--add-drop-table --skip-lock-tables --skip-add-locks --compress --skip-triggers --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_gp_bak --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_gp_import --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_practice_bak --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_practice_import &gt; IAPTus_Global.sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysql -u -p -h 10.0.2.54 -P 3306 &lt; .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysql -u -p -h 10.0.2.54 -P 3306 &lt; IAPTus_Global.sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ rm .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ rm IAPTus_Global.sql</div>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-11 15:07:14','2016-08-11 15:07:14',NULL),(60,31,19,'Deploy To Bournemouth','Commands for manually deploying to the iaptus bournemouth cluster','<h2>Release Managers Only</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When deploying to bournemouth there is currently an issue with re-syncing the code accross the cluster. This means that the deploy process actualy fails.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Untill the systems team fix the issue, the below commands will do what the automated script used to.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">\r\n<pre>\r\n<code>$ cd /var/www/html/iaptus-deploy-b/build/live\r\n\r\n$ rsync -rpKl &nbsp;--exclude &#39;backup/&#39; --exclude &#39;/build/&#39; --exclude &#39;.svn/&#39; --exclude &#39;.git/&#39; --exclude &#39;test/&#39; --exclude &#39;*.log&#39; --exclude &#39;logs/*&#39; &nbsp;--verbose --checksum --delete-after --ignore-errors --force --itemize-changes ../../ /var/www/html/iaptus\r\n\r\n$ rsync -rpKl &nbsp;--exclude &#39;backup/&#39; --exclude &#39;/build/&#39; --exclude &#39;.svn/&#39; --exclude &#39;.git/&#39; --exclude &#39;test/&#39; --exclude &#39;*.log&#39; --exclude &#39;logs/*&#39; &nbsp;--verbose --checksum --delete-after --ignore-errors --force --itemize-changes ../../ 192.168.63.32:/var/www/html/iaptus\r\n\r\n$ rsync -rpKl &nbsp;--exclude &#39;backup/&#39; --exclude &#39;/build/&#39; --exclude &#39;.svn/&#39; --exclude &#39;.git/&#39; --exclude &#39;test/&#39; --exclude &#39;*.log&#39; --exclude &#39;logs/*&#39; &nbsp;--verbose --checksum --delete-after --ignore-errors --force --itemize-changes ../../ 192.168.63.33:/var/www/html/iaptus\r\n\r\n$ curl 127.0.0.1/clear-cache.php</code></pre>\r\n</div>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-11 15:27:00','2016-08-11 15:27:00',NULL),(61,30,1,'Test Sites: Copying Data (Bmth to Brck)','Instructions for how to copy a live database from Bournemouth to a test site on Bracknell','<h3 style=\"color:#aaa; font-style:italic\">Please make sure you read and understand all these commands before executing them. This is the safest way of getting a bournmoth site to bracknell. This can be done at any time of the day as providing you do everything right there is very minimal risk.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Please replace the in the below commands with the details below:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SERVICE_DB_NAME</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Name of the DB you need to copy</li>\r\n	<li>e.g. IAPTus_IOW</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>DB_USER_NAME</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Your master DB user name</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PORT</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3306 for Set 4</li>\r\n	<li>3312 for Set 5</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ ssh iaptusvnode26</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ cd ~/</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysqldump -u -p -h 10.0.2.55 -P --add-drop-table --skip-lock-tables --skip-add-locks --compress --skip-triggers --ignore-table=.nh_stats_history --ignore-table=.nh_stats --ignore-table=.nh_user_activity_view --ignore-table=.nh_user_activity_edit &gt; .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysqldump -u -p -h 10.0.2.55 -P &nbsp;--add-drop-table --compress --no-data nh_stats --no-data nh_stats_history --no-data nh_user_activity_view --no-data nh_user_activity_edit &gt;&gt; .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysqldump IAPTus_Global -u -p -h 10.0.2.55 -P &nbsp;--add-drop-table --skip-lock-tables --skip-add-locks --compress --skip-triggers --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_gp_bak --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_gp_import --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_practice_bak --ignore-table=IAPTus_Global.nh_national_practice_import &gt; IAPTus_Global.sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysql -u -p -h 10.0.2.54 -P 3306 &lt; .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ mysql -u -p -h 10.0.2.54 -P 3306 &lt; IAPTus_Global.sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ rm .sql</div>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px 10px\">$ rm IAPTus_Global.sql</div>\r\n',1,6,'2016-08-11 15:42:56','2016-08-11 15:44:49',NULL),(62,31,19,'Deploying To Bournemouth','Commands for manually deploying to the iaptus bournemouth cluster','<h2>Release Managers Only</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>When deploying to bournemouth there is currently an issue with re-syncing the code accross the cluster. This means that the deploy process actualy fails.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Untill the systems team fix the issue, the below commands will do what the automated script used to.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#eee; border:1px solid #ccc; padding:5px