/li>\r\n	<li>Mention Dev Standards, branch naming conventions etc&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h1>Jira and Bamboo</h1>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Ask Jira admin to create Jira account</li>\r\n	<li>Explain the dashboard</li>\r\n	<li>Go to an issue (preferrably a well documented one!)\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>Explain the different types of issues</li>\r\n		<li>Explain which issues branch off where</li>\r\n		<li>Explain the workflow diagram</li>\r\n		<li>Explain the different fields</li>\r\n		<li>Definition of Done</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Ask Bamboo admin to create Bamboo account\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>Explain the difference between the different plans</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-18 12:56:53','2016-08-18 12:56:53',NULL),(69,32,23,'New Developer Setup','A few things to cover when getting a new starter set up in an iaptus team.','<h1>​Github and Virtual Machines</h1>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Register with Mayden 1Password and get set up to save passwords.</li>\r\n	<li>Create Github account\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>Ask Github admin to add to the developers group</li>\r\n		<li>Generate and install SSH key to access the Mayden repos (article <a href=\"https://help.github.com/articles/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent/\">here</a>).</li>\r\n		<li>Ask someone to explain some of the major repos - iaptus, postroom, paywall etc</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Download and install VirtualBox</li>\r\n	<li>Download and install Vagrant\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>Install vagrant vbguest plugin:&nbsp;vagrant plugin install vagrant-vbguest</li>\r\n		<li>Install vagrant hosts plugin: vagrant plugin install vagrant-hosts</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Download the iaptus&nbsp;PHP 5.6 Vagrant VM from the vagrant-vms repo</li>\r\n	<li>Run the vagrant up and vagrant ssh commands</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h1>iaptus</h1>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Build&nbsp;iaptus using the phing commands</li>\r\n	<li>Get the development front end logins from someone</li>\r\n	<li>Explore the repo - ask someone for a quick rundown of the key areas to look at</li>\r\n	<li>Talk through the different types of tests, how to run them</li>\r\n	<li>Get set up with a Database tool\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>Set up local database credentials</li>\r\n		<li>Log into database and point out key tables</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Mention Dev Standards, branch naming conventions etc&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h1>Jira and Bamboo</h1>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Ask Jira admin to create Jira account</li>\r\n	<li>Explain the dashboard</li>\r\n	<li>Go to an issue (preferrably a well documented one!)\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>Explain the different types of issues</li>\r\n		<li>Explain which issues branch off where</li>\r\n		<li>Explain the workflow diagram</li>\r\n		<li>Explain the different fields</li>\r\n		<li>Definition of Done</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Ask Bamboo admin to create Bamboo account\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>Explain the difference between the different plans</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-18 13:02:59','2016-08-18 13:02:59',NULL),(70,33,25,'Test!','TestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTest','<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;NOTE - the script discussed in this article is a legacy script that has been proposed for refactoring. The following explanation is correct at the time of writing in August 2016.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;h2&gt;Create new Service on Demo with Webtools&lt;/h2&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;The first step in setting up a new iaptus client is creating a new service on the demo site and database. This is usually done by the support team via a tools script that is accessible from the browser at &lt;a href=&quot;http://demo.iaptus.co.uk/webtools&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://demo.iaptus.co.uk/webtools&lt;/a&gt;. Once logged in one of the choices in the webtools menu is &amp;#39;Create New Service&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;When the &amp;#39;Create New Service&amp;#39; link is clicked it runs the following code from the iaptus codebase:&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;iaptus/tools/webtools/new_client_setup_live.php&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;The script requires you to back up existing demo tables, then displays a form for you to specify the service name and shortname and how many dummy users you want to create. You can also choose to create either an IAPT service or a CYP service.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;h2&gt;Code and script&lt;/h2&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;The&amp;nbsp;script creates a new service with the specified name by &lt;strong&gt;copying the settings of an existing &amp;#39;generic&amp;#39; service which has classic miniumum dataset settings. This generic service is hardcoded to service_id 6 &amp;nbsp;(service name &amp;quot;generic&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;on the demo site).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;h3&gt;Setupservice class&lt;/h3&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;The script instantiates an instance of class SetupService.class.php:&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;tools/webtools/setupscript/Setupservice.class.php&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;The script calls individual methods in this class to insert entries into each relevant table (e.g. nh_service, nh_fieldsSer, nh_list etc). &lt;strong&gt;Changes to this class may be needed when new required settings or tables are added to iaptus&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to ensure that new clients created by the script have the necessary data that will be added in patches for existing clients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;h2&gt;Instructions for Running Locally&lt;/h2&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;h3&gt;Configure the setup &amp;amp; database&lt;/h3&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;There is a setup.php file at &lt;code&gt;tools/webtools/inc/setup.php&lt;/code&gt; that gets created from setup_example.php when the build script runs. This file includes a require_once for a database file on our development setup at &lt;code&gt;/var/www/html/iaptus/includes/iaptusdevelopment/db_data_old_style.inc&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;Go to the db_data_old_style.inc file which sets up old style $db and $dbGlobal database connections. The build script currently sets both of these to the same database - the iaptus branch database. However our local setup now splits up the local and global iaptus databases to mirror the arrangement on our live servers. Change the following lines to the appropriate names of your local global and iaptus databases&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;... $dbs = [name of iaptus global database]&lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\n... $database = [name of iaptus database]&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;h3&gt;Change permissions on the backups folder&lt;/h3&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;Go to &lt;code&gt;iaptus/tools/webtools/setupscript&lt;/code&gt; and run the following (from host machine rather than in Vagrant box) to set the permissions to 777&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;chmod 777 backups&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;h3&gt;Change the &amp;#39;generic&amp;#39; service to copy from&lt;/h3&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;Service id 6 does not exist on our local testing iaptus databases so you need to change the following variables that appear near the top of new_client_setup_live.php&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;$copy_ser_id = 101;&lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\n$copy_team_id = 102;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\n$copy_area_id = 101;&lt;br /&gt;<br />\r\n$copy_shortName = &amp;quot;&amp;quot;;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;You should now be able to run the Create New Service script locally without any errors.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-18 15:37:14','2016-08-18 15:37:14',NULL),(71,33,25,'Test!','TestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTestTe