p;lt;/string&amp;gt;\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &amp;lt;/dict&amp;gt;\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &amp;lt;/array&amp;gt;\r\n&amp;lt;/dict&amp;gt;\r\n&amp;lt;/plist&amp;gt;\r\n\r\n</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-25 09:14:35','2016-08-25 09:14:35',NULL),(135,44,24,'Setting Up 1Password','Instructions for how to set up 1Password ','<p>At Mayden we use 1Password to store both personal and company authentication details in a secure and easily accessible way. 1Password will give you access to both a personal vault and also&nbsp;a Mayden team vault, which will enable you access to login details for things like the Demo iaptus site, databases and company ecommerce accounts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow these steps to get set up:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Sign Up for a 1Password Account</li>\r\n	<li>Download and Set Up 1Password Desktop App</li>\r\n	<li>Request a Mayden Team Vault invite from a member of the SysOps team</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Signing Up for a 1Password Account</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To sign up for a 1Password account, go <a href=\"https://start.1password.com/signup/team?type=I\">here</a>..</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow the sign up dialogs, opting for a personal account when prompted, and making a note of your 1Password key</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Downloading and Setting Up 1Password Desktop App</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Download and install the software for your operating system <a href=\"https://agilebits.com/downloads\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Open the program and log in using the details you got from step 1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Request a Mayden Team Vault Invite</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Ask a member of the SysOps team to send you an email invite to the Mayden Vault. The current designated 1Password Guru is Matt E.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow the instructions in the email invite and follow the dialogs.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Notes</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maintain a distinction between your personal vault and the Mayden vault or you&#39;ll end up sharing your private details with the whole company!</li>\r\n	<li>You may also want to download the <a href=\"https://agilebits.com/onepassword/extensions\">1Password browser plugin</a>, which can autofill website forms for you.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-25 12:58:12','2016-08-25 12:58:12',NULL),(136,51,30,'1Password: Importing Keepass Vault','How to import the credentials in your Keepass into a 1Password vault','<p>If you have credentials stored in your Keepass software, this can be exported and then imported into 1Password. You will need access to your Keepass vault, the&nbsp;1Password software and a personal 1Password Vault. If you need help setting up the 1Password software you can reference <a href=\"http://black-box.mayden.co.uk/p/new-starters/set-up/setting-up-1password\">this page</a>. To import your Keepass credentials, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Export your Keepass vault as XML</li>\r\n	<li>Convert your Keepass XML file to a 1Password compatible file&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Import your 1Password compatible file to 1Password</li>\r\n	<li>Super destroy Your Keepass XML and 1Password compatible files</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Exporting Your Keepass Vault as XML</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Open Keepass and begin the export process by clicking on File &gt; Export. Then click the &#39;Keepass XML (2.x)&#39; option, select an &#39;Export to&#39; directory and click &#39;Ok&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Converting Your Keepass XML File to a 1Password Compatible File</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You can use Mayden&#39;s handy Keepass conversion tool to convert your Keepass XML file. To do this, go to <a href=\"http://cloud4.may:8011/\">the conversion tool</a> and use it to upload the XML file you exported from Keepass. On hitting the &#39;Upload XML File&#39; button, a download should begin. This is your 1Password compatible file.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Importing Your 1Password Compatible File into 1Password</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mac:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Open the 1Password software</li>\r\n		<li>Click File &gt; Import...</li>\r\n		<li>Make sure &#39;Other&#39; is select under &#39;Where is your data coming from&#39;, and click &#39;Import a 1PIF file&#39;</li>\r\n		<li>Select your destination vault (that you want to import your credentials into) and select the file you want to import</li>\r\n		<li>Follow the dialog to finish the import process</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Windows:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Open the 1Password software</li>\r\n		<li>Click the gear icon in the top left of the 1Password window</li>\r\n		<li>Click &#39;Import&#39;</li>\r\n		<li>Select your destination vault (that you want to import your credentials into) and select the file you want to import</li>\r\n		<li>Follow the dialog to finish the import process</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>​</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Linux:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Puzzle through it on your own and document it here</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4.&nbsp;Super Destory Your Keepass XML and 1Password Compatible Files</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have ascertained that your passwords have been imported successfully, obliterate your Keepass XML file and 1Password compatible file&nbsp;as they contain super secret things and leaving them lying around completely defeats the point of having a password manager. The end.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-25 13:22:39','2016-08-25 13:22:39',NULL),(137,51,30,'1Password: Importing Keepass Vault','How to import the credentials in your Keepass into a 1Password vault','<p>If you have credentials stored in your Keepass software, this can be exported and then imported into 1Password. You will need access to your Keepass vault, the&nbsp;1Password software and a personal 1Password Vault. If you need help setting up the 1Password software you can reference <a href=\"http://black-box.mayden.co.uk/p/new-starters/set-up/setting-up-1password\">this page</a>. To import your Keepass credentials, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Export your Keepass vault as XML</li>\r\n	<li>Convert your Keepass XML file to a 1Password compatible file&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Import your 1Password compatible file to 1Password</li>\r\n	<li>Super destroy Your Keepass XML and 1Password compatible files</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Exporting Your Keepass Vault as XML</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Open Keepass and begin the export process by clicking on File &gt; Export. Then click the &#39;Keepass XML (2.x)&#39; option, select an &#39;Export to&#39; directory and click &#39;Ok&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Converting Your Keepass XML File to a 1Password Compatible File</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>You can use Mayden&#39;s handy Keepass conversion tool to convert your Keepass XML file. To do this, go to <a href=\"http://cloud4.may:8011/\">the conversion tool</a> and use it to upload the XML file you exported from Keepass. On hitting the &#39;Upload XML File&#39; button, a download should begin. This is your 1Password compatible file.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>3. Importing Your 1Password Compatible File into 1Password</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Mac:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Open the 1Password software</li>\r\n		<li>Click File &gt; Import...</li>\r\n		<li>Make sure &#39;Other&#39; is select under &#39;Where is your data coming from&#39;, and click &#39;Import a 1PIF file&#39;</li>\r\n		<li>Select your destination vault (that you want to import your credentials into) and select the file you want to import</li>\r\n		<li>Follow the dialog to finish the import process</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Windows:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Open the 1Password software</li>\r\n		<li>Click the gear icon in the top left of the 1Password window</li>\r\n		<li>Click &#39;Import&#39;</li>\r\n		<li>Select your destination vault (that you want to import your credentials into) and select the file you want to import</li>\r\n		<li>Follow the dialog to finish the import process</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>​</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Linux:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Puzzle through it on your own and document it here</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>4.&nbsp;Super Destroy Your Keepass XML and 1Password Compatible Files</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Once you have ascertained that your passwords have been imported successfully, obliterate your Keepass XML file and 1Password compatible file&nbsp;as they contain super secret things and leaving them lying around completely defeats the point of having a password manager. The end.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,19,'2016-08-25 13:29:24','2016-08-25 13:44:59',NULL),(138,44,24,'Setting Up 1Password','Instructions for how to set up 1Password ','<p>At Mayden we use 1Password to store both personal and company authentication details in a secure and easily accessible way. 1Password will give you access to both a personal vault and also&nbsp;a Mayden team vault, which will enable you access to login details for things like the Demo iaptus site, databases and company ecommerce accounts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow these steps to get set up:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Request a Mayden Team Vault Invite and Register</li>\r\n	<li>Download and Set Up 1Password Desktop App</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Request a Mayden Team Vault Invite and Register</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Ask a member of the SysOps team to send you an email invite to the Mayden Vault. The current designated 1Password Guru is Matt E.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Follow the instructions in the email invite and follow the dialogs. This should guide you through registering with your name and generating a secret key and password. You should store your secret key somewhere safe.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>2. Downloading and Setting Up 1Password Desktop App</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Download and install the software for your operating system <a href=\"https://agilebits.com/downloads\">here</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Open the program and log in using the details you got from step 1, using &#39;mayden.1password.com&#39;&nbsp;as the sign-in address</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Notes</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Maintain a distinction between your personal vault and the Mayden vault or you&#39;ll end up sharing your private details with the whole company!</li>\r\n	<li>You may also want to download the <a href=\"https://agilebits.com/onepassword/extensions\">1Password browser plugin</a>, which can autofill website forms for you.&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>If you want to import your Keepass store to 1Password, there are instructions for this <a href=\"http://black-box.mayden.co.uk/p/mayden/software-tools/1password-importing-keepass-vault\">here</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,1,'2016-08-25 14:17:09','2016-08-25 14:17:09',NULL),(139,51,30,'1Password: Importing Keepass Vault','How to import the credentials in your Keepass into a 1Password vault','<p>If you have credentials stored in your Keepass software, this can be exported and then imported into 1Password. You will need access to your Keepass vault, the&nbsp;1Password software and a personal 1Password Vault. If you need help setting up the 1Password software you can reference <a href=\"http://black-box.mayden.co.uk/p/new-starters/set-up/setting-up-1password\">this page</a>. To import your Keepass credentials, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Export your Keepass vault as XML</li>\r\n	<li>Convert your Keepass XML file to a 1Password compatible file&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Import your 1Password compatible file to 1Password</li>\r\n	<li>Super destroy your Keepass XML and 1Password compatible files</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>1. Exporting Your Keepass Vault as XML<