 the data is used in national reporting and the codes and information is from the national data published by the HSCIC, but for&nbsp;individual GPs the data and gp codes are not necessarily unique and the gp_code entries cannot be relied upon</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Database Storage</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Shared Database&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The shared database contains tables <strong>nh_national_practice</strong> and <strong>nh_national_gp</strong>. These tables contain national gp practice and national general practitioner data derived from national data released&nbsp;by the HSCIC and updated at quarterly intervals. <em>Previously these tables were located on the iaptus Global databases and at the time of writing there are still copies there - these are not being updated and will be removed in the future when we are certain everything in iaptus is using the Shared Database source without any issues.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Iaptus Databases</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>nh_gp_serPractice</strong> : this table contains the gp practices that are turned on for a particular service. It has a local_pr_id autoincrement column which provides the local_pr_id values that are used everywhere else in the database to identify practices. The pr_id column relates to different things depending on the local_entry column value:&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"1\" style=\"width:800px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Local entry value</td>\r\n			<td>pr_id value</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>1</td>\r\n			<td>pr_id is FK from pr_id column in nh_gp_local_practice (see below)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>0</td>\r\n			<td>pr_id is FK from pr_id column in nh_national_practice table in Shared database (see above)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>If local_entry is 0 (ie. relates to practice from nh_national_practice table on Shared database) then the data should match national data in the shared database and the superuser tools will only allow national practices to be added or deleted - not amended (except for &quot;nicknames&quot;).&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>nh_gp_local_practice</strong>: this table contains data for &quot;practices&quot;&nbsp;that are not in the national gp data that comes from the HSCIC. Iaptus services can create entries in here using&nbsp;the &#39;Local Sources&#39; section of the GP Practice Manager Tool. The two instances where you usually have local sources are:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>GP referrals from institutions that are not a normal GP practice on the national register (e.g. army base referral); &nbsp;and</li>\r\n	<li>old entries that could not be successfully matched against a national practice when iaptus moved to using the official national GP Practice&nbsp;data a few years back and all practices already present in the iaptus databases&nbsp;were mapped across to the correct national practice. Practice codes in this table are optional and may not be accurate even when present.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>nh_gp</strong> : this table contains individual gp data and each GP row is linked to a single gp practice. The auto-increment gp_id column from this table is used everywhere else in the database to identify individual gps.&nbsp;When a national gp practice is added to an iaptus service initially a list of gps with gp_codes for that practice are imported at the same time. Thereafter this data can be freely updated however via front end tools (see GP Practice Manager) and gp codes and data cannot be relied upon as matching national data.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>nh_gp_group</strong>: defines groups of gp practices which can be created by iaptus services using front end superuser tools (see GP Practice Manager)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>nh_gp_groupPractice</strong>: link table which links local_pr_ids to gp groups (see nh_gp_group above)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>GP Practice Manager</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The superuser GP Practice Manager tool allows clients to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Add and remove national GP Practices to their local iaptus instance from the national GP Practice&nbsp;data (see Shared database above)</li>\r\n	<li>Create Local Sources for &quot;practices&quot; unavailable in the national data</li>\r\n	<li>Create and remove GP Practice Groups and assign and remove practices / local sources to the groups</li>\r\n	<li>Amend individual GP details attached to any practices or local sources</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Client Requests to Amend or Add Practices&nbsp;</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In the past we used to amend practice data that was wrong in the HSCIC updates and add new practices in advance of them being included in the next quarterly HSCIC update. <strong>We no longer do this - clients should contact the HSCIC directly for corrections to existing entries or wait for the next quarterly update to be released if a new practice is missing.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The national practice lists are currently updated by the Data Services team - queries about when the next update is due and if a specific practice or correction appears in it may be referred to that team. The update download and processing script is currently run manually, but may be turned into a fully automated process on the server in the near future.</p>\r\n',1,30,'2016-09-07 16:24:42','2016-09-07 16:24:42',NULL),(156,58,7,'National GP Practices and GPs','Information about the national GP practices and GP and practice information in the system','<p>Iaptus handles both GP practice and individual GP data. <strong>For practices the data is used in national reporting and the codes and information is from the national data published by the HSCIC, but for&nbsp;individual GPs the data and gp codes are not necessarily unique and the gp_code entries cannot be relied upon</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Database Storage</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Shared Database&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>The shared database contains tables <strong>nh_national_practice</strong> and <