nbsp;--exclude \'backup/\' --exclude \'/build/\' --exclude \'.svn/\' --exclude \'.git/\' --exclude \'test/\' --exclude \'*.log\' --exclude \'logs/*\' &amp;nbsp;--verbose --checksum --delete-after --ignore-errors --force --itemize-changes ../../ 192.168.63.33:/var/www/html/iaptus\r\n\r\n$ curl 127.0.0.1/clear-cache.php&lt;/code&gt;</pre>\r\n\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-13 16:13:52','2016-09-13 16:13:52',NULL),(210,31,19,'Deploying To Bournemouth','Commands for manually deploying to the iaptus bournemouth cluster','<h2>Release Managers Only</h2>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<p>When deploying to bournemouth there is currently an issue with re-syncing the code accross the cluster. This means that the deploy process actualy fails.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Untill the systems team fix the issue, the below commands will do what the automated script used to.</p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n$ cd /var/www/html/iaptus-deploy-b/build/live\r\n\r\n$ rsync -rpKl &nbsp;--exclude \'backup/\' --exclude \'/build/\' --exclude \'.svn/\' --exclude \'.git/\' --exclude \'test/\' --exclude \'*.log\' --exclude \'logs/*\' &nbsp;--verbose --checksum --delete-after --ignore-errors --force --itemize-changes ../../ /var/www/html/iaptus\r\n\r\n$ rsync -rpKl &nbsp;--exclude \'backup/\' --exclude \'/build/\' --exclude \'.svn/\' --exclude \'.git/\' --exclude \'test/\' --exclude \'*.log\' --exclude \'logs/*\' &nbsp;--verbose --checksum --delete-after --ignore-errors --force --itemize-changes ../../ 192.168.63.32:/var/www/html/iaptus\r\n\r\n$ rsync -rpKl &nbsp;--exclude \'backup/\' --exclude \'/build/\' --exclude \'.svn/\' --exclude \'.git/\' --exclude \'test/\' --exclude \'*.log\' --exclude \'logs/*\' &nbsp;--verbose --checksum --delete-after --ignore-errors --force --itemize-changes ../../ 192.168.63.33:/var/www/html/iaptus\r\n\r\n$ curl 127.0.0.1/clear-cache.php</pre>\r\n\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-13 16:14:02','2016-09-13 16:14:02',NULL),(211,52,31,'Set up Local Development Environment','how to get a local copy of the bacpac application with a virtual machine and get everything working','<p>You will need:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Access to the Mayden Github bacpac repository and appropriate SSH keys installed</li>\r\n	<li>Vagrant software installed on your laptop</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of the Mayden <a href=\"https://github.com/may-den/vagrant-vms\" target=\"_blank\">vagrant-vms</a> repository from GitHub</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Create a folder in an appropriate place on your computer called \'bacpac\' and move into that directory</li>\r\n	<li>Create a folder within the bacpac folder called html and move into that directory</li>\r\n	<li>Do <code>git clone&nbsp;ssh://sls@slsapp.com:1234/mayden/bacpac.git</code> in the html directory </li>\r\n	<li>Go to up to date copy of the Mayden vagrant-vms repository and get a copy of the Vagrantfile from the bacpac directory in that repository. Copy the vagrantfile into the bacpac directory created at step 1. above.</li>\r\n	<li>Edit the Vagrantfile from step 3. as follows: <code>config.vm.network &quot;private_network&quot;, ip: &quot;192.168.20.31&quot;</code></li>\r\n	<li>Use the <code>vagrant up</code> command to start the vagrant box from inside the top level bacpac directory created at step 1.</li>\r\n	<li>When the machine is up and ready (you will need to enter your password to permit the file syncing with the Vagrant box) go to the bacpac code folder (<em>still in your host machine</em>) and do composer install<br />\r\n	<code>cd html/bacpac; chmod +x composer.phar;&nbsp;./composer.phar install; cd -</code></li>\r\n	<li>Use the <code>vagrant ssh</code> command to start a shell session to the vagrant box</li>\r\n	<li>From within the vagrant box go to /var/www/html/bacpac/build directory and create a new file <code>build.properties</code> at the same level as the build.properties.example file. Copy the contents from the section below (build.properties) into the new build.properties file. </li>\r\n	<li>From within the build folder in t