c code folder (<em>still in your host machine</em>) and do composer install<br />\r\n    <code>cd html/bacpac;</code><br />\r\n    <code>chmod +x composer.phar;&nbsp;./composer.phar install;</code><br />\r\n    <code>cd -</code></li></code><br />\r\n    <li>Use the <code>vagrant ssh</code> command to start a shell session to the vagrant box</li>\r\n    <li>From within the vagrant box go to /var/www/html/bacpac/build directory and create a new file <code>build.properties</code> at the same level as the build.properties.example file. Copy the contents from the section below (build.properties) into the new build.properties file. </li>\r\n    <li>From within the build folder in the vagrant box run <code>ant rebuild</code></li>\r\n    <li>Still in the vagrant box go to /etc/httpd/conf.d and edit the bacpac.conf file so that the DocumentRoot is <code>/var/www/html/bacpac/public</code> and change the Directory path two lines below to match</li>\r\n    <li>Restart the apache server for the changes in step 11 to take effect.</li>\r\n    <li>Update /etc/hosts file on your local machine - add following: \r\n    <ul><li class=\"no-bullet\"><pre>\r\n192.168.20.31 bacpac.dev\r\n192.168.20.31 bacpac.test\r\n192.168.20.31 paywall.dev\r\n192.168.20.31 paywall.test</pre></li></ul>\r\n    You should now be able to go to  the URL bacpac.dev in a browser on your host machine and see the bacpac login page.</li>\r\n    <li>Login details:<br />\r\n    email: chris.eldridge@mayden.co.uk,<br />\r\n    password: well known password</li>\r\n    <li>To connect to the bacpac databases running in the vagrant box (for example with Sequel Pro) on your host machine use host: 127.0.0.1  <strong>port: 4040</strong>  username: root  password: vagrant</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<br />\r\n<h3>build.properties</h3>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><pre>db.username=root&lt;br /&gt;\r\ndb.ip=127.0.0.1&lt;br /&gt;\r\ndb.host=localhost&lt;br /&gt;\r\ndb.password=vagrant&lt;br /&gt;\r\ndb.database=bacp_trunk&lt;br /&gt;\r\ndb.test_databas