c-pac.co.uk/referral/</pre></p>\r\n\r\n<p> </p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-13 16:20:44','2016-09-13 16:20:44',NULL),(215,22,16,'Configuring Test Sites For Self Referral Testing','Setup steps for test sites in order to test Self Referrals','<p>1. Follow <a href=\"http://black-box.mayden.co.uk/p/mayden/servers/deploying-test-sites\">these instructions</a> on setting up a test site</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Follow <a href=\"http://black-box.mayden.co.uk/p/mayden/servers/copying-live-data-to-test-sites\">these instructions</a> on copying a live database to the test site</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Configure the test site for use with self referrals (datacentre agnostic)</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>On the server containing your chosen iaptus test site, go to <code>/var/www/html/iaptustest-testing-XX/cron_live </code>and in<code> cron_setup.php </code>modify the Postroom URL to point at a testing postroom, e.g. https://postroomtest-a3.iaptus.nhs.uk</li>\r\n	<li>Edit <code>cron_config.php</code> and uncomment the \"<code>CronSelfReferrals</code>\" lines</li>\r\n	<li>On the server containing your test postroom (note, MAY be a different server to where your test site is), go to<code> /var/www/html/postroomtest-xx/cron</code></li>\r\n	<li>Modify <code>postroom_cron_config.php</code> and uncomment the lines regarding \"<code>SelfReferralsMaydenTask</code>\"</li>\r\n	<li>In the test postroom database, (api_testXX) add the service id and the form UUID (see other article) to the service_config table​</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Once the test referral has been submitted, run the following command in the test postroom root folder: \"<code>php public/index.php cron process</code>\". Once run successfully the data will appear in the collection_box table of the database. Re-comment the <code>postroom_cron_config.php</code>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Go back to your iaptus test site and go to <code>/var/www/html/iaptustest-testing-XX/cron_live</code> and run: \"<code>php cron.php</code>\". When done, re-comment out the lines in cron config.</p>\r\n',1,29,'2016-09-14 08:31:21','2016-09-14 08:37:58',NULL),(216,21,30,'Sequel Pro: Connection Favourites','Database favourites that can be imported into Sequel Pro.','<p>To import standard Mayden favourites into Sequal Pro, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Quit Sequel Pro if it’s running</li>\r\n	<li>Replace ~/Library/Application Support/Sequel Pro/Data/Favourites.plist with a file containing the XML below</li>\r\n	<li>Start up Sequel Pro again</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<pre>\r\n&lt;!--?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?--&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;plist version=&quot;1.0&quot;&gt;\r\n&lt;dict&gt;\r\n    &lt;key&gt;SPConnectionFavorites&lt;/key&gt;\r\n    &lt;array&gt;\r\n        &lt;dict&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;database&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;host&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;127.0.0.1&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;id&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;integer&gt;-29180194521444731&lt;/integer&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;name&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;bacpac-live via bpvnode15&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;port&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;13306&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;socket&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;sshHost&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;sshKeyLocation&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;sshKeyLocationEnabled&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;integer&gt;0&lt;/integer&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;sshPort&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;sshUser&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;sslCACertFileLocation&lt;/key&gt;\r\n            &lt;string&gt;&lt;/string&gt;\r\n            &lt;key&gt;sslCACertFileLocationEnabled&lt;/key&gt;\r\n        