4 09:23:54',NULL),(218,20,18,'MTA Adding New Hosts','How to add new hosts to mtavnode16 and mtavnode21:','<h3>iptables:</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n# Check current iptables status \r\nsudo iptables -L INPUT -n --line-numbers \r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<p># Add a new rule (using correct source IP -s 192.168.10.10 etc) sudo iptables -I INPUT 4 -m state --state NEW -m tcp -p tcp -s *.*.*.* --dport 25 -j ACCEPT</p>\r\n\r\n<p># Save iptables when done (otherwise the next restart will drop your new rules) sudo service iptables save</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>sendmail</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\ncd /etc/mail\r\nsudo nano /etc/mail/access\r\n# Add new source host IP into access list\r\nsudo make\r\nsudo service sendmail restart\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<h3>Source host, redirect mail to mta</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nsudo nano /etc/sysconfig/sendmail\r\nDAEMON=no\r\n\r\nsudo nano /etc/mail/submit.cf\r\nD{MTAHost}[192.168.60.16]   (Or 192.168.60.21)</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:25:48','2016-09-14 09:25:48',NULL),(219,17,19,'Fixing replication error between Master & Slave DBs','Replication error on multi masters','<h2>Replication Error On Multi Masters</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>See also&nbsp;<a href=\"/p/iaptus/devops/db-replication-monitoring\">Db Replication Monitoring</a>&nbsp;for notes on how replication is monitored.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Connect to PRTG monitor vm ivnode14(BRCK) or ivnode7(BMTH)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Connect to db server reporting issue</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On monitor vm:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\ncd /var/www/html/iaptus-deploy/monitoring/dbHeartbeat/</pre>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nphp dbStatus.php</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Shows what the status monitor thinks is going on</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Marked down by monitoring - says iaptus cannot connect to those db\'s on that ip</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; The :1 after DB name&nbsp;is the connection type - positive numbers mean master r/w connections</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Negative numbers mean slave (ro) connections</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nphp dbControl.php</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Lets you override the automatic monitoring, you can remove and restore access to databases from here for maintaince</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2 - take a host out (it will ask you to confirm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 3 - put it back in (It will set it to failed by monitoring and will only restore when monitoring says all clear based on replication status)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 4 - Reset status cache - wipes the monitoring status if it gets tangled up</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; 2 &amp; 3 are pretty safe, 4 is dangerous</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; There\'s another layer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Manual override is higher precedence than automated monitoring</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; But iaptus has a lower precedence layer as well - in case monitoring isn\'t running.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; If iaptus detects a db down, it will \"mark down by iaptus\" for 60 seconds and then retry on the next request</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nphp dbMonitor.php id=ivnode19</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; This is the sensor - used by PRTG and monitoring</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Measured lag is important, as is the Status</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Status is only [1] if all the following status are [1], so it\'s a quick visual check</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; If replication crashes, then the error will also be printed here which I find quicker than show slave status in the db and then scrolling right for 30s to find the column</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Also a status[0] triggers PRTG alert</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>connect to mysql in HeidiSQL</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Only kill select / read queries</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Killing queries that change data crashes replication and creates pain</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; Copy the query first, then add query to task list&nbsp;<a href=\"https://crm.mayden.co.uk/tasks/52720/\">#52720</a>&nbsp;noting the service and run time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>you can check the db monitor tool logs at http://logs.iaptus.nhs.uk/#/dashboard/elasticsearch/Error%20Logs</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:26:37','2016-09-14 09:26:37',NULL),(220,15,1,'Server Map Diagram','A diagram showing the iaptus servers, their associated modules and databases, and places where communication happens between servers and modules.','<div class=\"diagram\">\r\n<div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:auto;width:100%;\">\r\n<div style=\"width:1px;height:1px;overflow:hidden;\"></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:29:40','2016-09-14 09:29:40',NULL),(221,15,1,'Server Map Diagram','A diagram showing the iaptus servers, their associated modules and databases, and places where communication happens between servers and modules.','<div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"max-width:100%;\" data-mxgraph=\"{&quot;highlight&quot;:&quot;#0000ff&quot;,&quot;nav&quot;:true,&quot;edit&quot;:&quot;_blank&quot;,&quot;xml&quot;:&quot;&lt;mxfile userAgent=\\&quot;Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36\\&quot; version=\\&quot;5.6.0.5\\&quot; editor=\\&quot;www.draw.io\\&quot; type=\\&quot;google\\&quot;&gt;&lt;diagram&gt;&lt;/diagram&gt;&lt;/mxfile&gt;&quot;}\"></div>',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:30:28','2016-09-14 09:30:28',NULL),(222,15,1,'Server Map Diagram','A diagram showing the iaptus servers, their associated modules and databases, and places where communication happens between servers and modules.','<div class=\"diagram\">\r\n<div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"max-width:100%;\" data-mxgraph=\"{&quot;highlight&quot;:&quot;#0000ff&quot;,&quot;nav&quot;:true,&quot;edit&quot;:&quot;_blank&quot;,&quot;xml&quot;:&quot;&lt;mxfile userAgent=\\&quot;Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36\\&quot; version=\\&quot;5.6.0.5\\&quot; editor=\\&quot;www.draw.io\\&quot; type=\\&quot;google\\&quot;&gt;&lt;diagram&gt;&lt;/diagram&gt;&lt;/mxfile&gt;&quot;}\"></div></div>',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:31:22','2016-09-14 09:31:22',NULL),(223,15,1,'Server Map Diagram','A diagram showing the iaptus servers, their associated modules and databases, and places where communication happens between servers and modules.','<div class=\"diagram\"><div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"max-width:100%;\" data-mxgraph=\"{\"highlight\":\"#0000ff\",\"nav\":true,\"edit\":\"_blank\",\"xml\":\"<mxfile userAgent=\\\"Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36\\\" version=\\\"5.6.0.5\\\" editor=\\\"www.draw.io\\\" type=\\\"google\\\"><diagram></diagram></mxfile>\"}\"></div></div>',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:35:36','2016-09-14 09:35:36',NULL),(224,48,29,'Manually Removing Care Pathway Links','How to remove a link from a care pathway so it no longer appears on the care pathway tools','<p>Where care pathway diagrams are too large to load in the care pathway diagram tool, it may be necessary manually remove links from care pathways. This must be done on the Demo site and the link itself must <strong>not&nbsp;</strong>be deleted - only archived/\'olded\'.&nbsp;To do so, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>To start, you will need the IDs of the care pathway stages for which the link needs deleting. You should locate the stages in the nh_stage table for which the link between needs to be removed, making note of the ID for the \'from\' stage (where the patient would start out) and the ID for the \'to\' stage (where the patient could progress to). Make sure you have selected the stage for the correct service using the ser_id column.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Next, use these IDs to find the link in the nh_stage_process table and change the live column from <code>1</code> to <code>0</code>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>UPDATE nh_stage_process SET live=0 WHERE stage_from=STAGE_FROM_ID AND stage_to=STAGE_TO_ID;</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you need to set the link in the XML to archived too. You can find the XML in the&nbsp;nh_diagram table. Open the XML in a text editor and locate&nbsp;the link which needs archiving. You will be able to find it by removing the service id and \'00\' from the beginning of the STAGE_FROM&nbsp;ID and&nbsp;STAGE_TO_ID and looking for the link with a source and target with this number in it. For example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>SERVICE_ID = 160</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>STAGE_FROM_ID = 1600022</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>STAGE_TO_ID = 1600044</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To archive the link, simply replace the&nbsp;<code>archived=&quot;0&quot;</code> part with&nbsp;<code>archived=&quot;1&quot;:</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you need to check that it is no longer possible travel between the two stages in the Care Pathway section on iaptus. When you have a patient in the \'stage from\' stage, it should not be possible to process the patient onto the \'to stage\' as you removed the link.</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:40:19','2016-09-14 09:40:19',NULL),(225,48,29,'Manually Removing Care Pathway Links','How to remove a link from a care pathway so it no longer appears on the care pathway tools','<p>Where care pathway diagrams are too large to load in the care pathway diagram tool, it may be necessary manually remove links from care pathways. This must be done on the Demo site and the link itself must <strong>not&nbsp;</strong>be deleted - only archived/\'olded\'.&nbsp;To do so, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>To start, you will need the IDs of the care pathway stages for which the link needs deleting. You should locate the stages in the nh_stage table for which the link between needs to be removed, making note of the ID for the \'from\' stage (where the patient would start out) and the ID for the \'to\' stage (where the patient could progress to). Make sure you have selected the stage for the correct service using the ser_id column.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Next, use these IDs to find the link in the nh_stage_process table and change the live column from <code>1</code> to <code>0</code>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>UPDATE nh_stage_process SET live=0 WHERE stage_from=STAGE_FROM_ID AND stage_to=STAGE_TO_ID;</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you need to set the link in the XML to archived too. You can find the XML in the&nbsp;nh_diagram table. Open the XML in a text editor and locate&nbsp;the link which needs archiving. You will be able to find it by removing the service id and \'00\' from the beginning of the STAGE_FROM&nbsp;ID and&nbsp;STAGE_TO_ID and looking for the link with a source and target with this number in it. For example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>SERVICE_ID = 160</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>STAGE_FROM_ID = 1600022</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>STAGE_TO_ID = 1600044</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To archive the link, simply replace the&nbsp;<code>archived=&quot;0&quot;</code> part with&nbsp;<code>archived=&quot;1&quot;:</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you need to check that it is no longer possible travel between the two stages in the Care Pathway section on iaptus. When you have a patient in the \'stage from\' stage, it should not be possible to process the patient onto the \'to stage\' as you removed the link.</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:40:29','2016-09-14 09:40:29',NULL),(226,49,29,'Manually Adding Care Pathway Links','How to add a link from a care pathway so it appears on the care pathway tools','<p>Where care pathway diagrams are too large to load in the care pathway diagram tool, it may be necessary manually add links to care pathways. This must be done on the Demo. To do so, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>To start, you will need the IDs of the care pathway stages for which the link needs adding. You should locate the stages in the nh_stage table for which the link between needs to be added, making note of the ID for the \'from\' stage (where the patient would start out) and the ID for the \'to\' stage (where the patient could progress to). Make sure you have selected the stage for the correct service using the ser_id column.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You will also need to find your next LINK_ID -&nbsp;this should be the next autoincrement value in the nh_stage_process table, e.g. if the highest existing id is 2000, your link ID will be 2001&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Next, you need to write the XML for your new link:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>&amp;lt;link id=&amp;quot;LINK_ID&amp;quot; name=&amp;quot;lineLINK_ID&amp;quot; direction=&amp;quot;down&amp;quot; source=&amp;quot;rectangleSTAGE_FROM_ID&amp;quot; target=&amp;quot;rectangleSTAGE_TO_ID&amp;quot; xCoords=&amp;quot;0,0&amp;quot; yCoords=&amp;quot;0,0&amp;quot; hidden=&amp;quot;0&amp;quot; archived=&amp;quot;0&amp;quot;/&amp;gt;</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>For example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>&amp;lt;link id=&amp;quot;200&amp;quot; name=&amp;quot;line200&amp;quot; direction=&amp;quot;down&amp;quot; source=&amp;quot;rectangle22&amp;quot; target=&amp;quot;rectangle44&amp;quot; xCoords=&amp;quot;0,0&amp;quot; yCoords=&amp;quot;0,0&amp;quot; hidden=&amp;quot;0&amp;quot; archived=&amp;quot;0&amp;quot;/&amp;gt;</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>These links then need to be added to the XML file for this service in the latest non-auto-saved nh_diagram row. It should be appended to the section with the other links in.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This adds the links to the care pathway diagram tool. To carry these changes over to the iaptus care pathway section, you should&nbsp;export the SQL from the Mayden Care Pathway Tool (as you would when putting a care pathway live) and run the resulting SQL on demo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you need to check that it is now possible to travel between the two stages in the Care Pathway section on iaptus using your link. When you have a patient in the \'stage from\' stage, it should now&nbsp;be possible to process the patient onto the \'to stage\' as you removed the link.</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:41:42','2016-09-14 09:41:42',NULL),(227,54,17,'Copy New Service From Demo DB to Live DB','Information about the tools folder scripts that are used when copying the relevant data for a new service from the demo database (which has all services) to a live database (with just the data for the new service which is going live). (For information about the Dev-Ops system team work in setting up a new database on the live server and registering the new domain etc see Dev-Ops->iaptus->Setup new IAPTus live sites.)','<p><em>NOTE - the script discussed in this article is a legacy script that has been proposed for refactoring. The following explanation is correct at the time of writing in August 2016.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Create New Single Service Database to go Live</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>When a client has approved their demo site developers need to get the relevant data from the demo database for that service and create an iaptus single service live database to be copied to the live server</strong>. Relevant entries for the global database relating to the new service also need to be run on the live global databases. This is all done using scripts located in <code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools</code> folder that are run locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Running the copy demo to live script</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Export whole iaptus demo database from the demo server&nbsp;as mysqldump and then import locally to Vagrant box.</li>\r\n	<li>Rename local copy demo database to \"<code>iaptus_demo_bak&quot;.</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new empty local database called&nbsp; \"<code>iaptus_new_client&quot;</code></li>\r\n	<li>Checkout up to date copy of the iaptus codebase (master) and go to the file at <code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data_example.inc</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new file&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data.inc</code> by copying db_data_example.inc</li>\r\n	<li>Edit the db_data_example.inc file so that it contains valid database&nbsp;details to create the $dbDemoBak and $dbNewClient connections to local databases iaptus_demo_bak and iaptus_new_client (see above)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to&nbsp;file at&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/inc/setup_example.php</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new file&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/inc/setup.php</code>&nbsp;by copying setup_example.php</li>\r\n	<li>Edit setup.php so that it looks like setup.php below</li>\r\n	<li>In your browser go to your vagrant iaptus URL and append the path to the following file: iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/new_client.php. You should see a page of links to various New Client Setup tools.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the link labelled 2. New Client Setup. You should then get choices at the bottom. Check target and source databases, choose IAPT or&nbsp;CYP as appropriate and choose the appropriate service from the drop down list. Click Setup button. The database script should then put all the appropriate data into the iaptus_new_client database and you should also be given some SQL insert statements to be run on the Global iaptus databases for service specific entries from the demo global database tables.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>setup.php</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/includes/iaptusdevelopment/db_data_old_style.inc\');\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data.inc\');\r\ndefine(\'SCORING_CLASS_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/html/forms/scoring/\');\r\ndefine(\'MYSQL_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/tools/importTool/mysql/\');\r\ndefine(\'IAPTUS_PATH\', \'/iaptus/trunk/html\');\r\nfunction checkDBError(&amp;$DBObject)\r\n{\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; if (PEAR::isError($DBObject))\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; {\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $trace=debug_backtrace();\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; $report=str_replace(\'/var/www/html/\', \'\', $trace[0][\'file\']).\' Line: \'.$trace[0][\'line\'].\' Msg: \'.$DBObject---&gt;getDebugInfo(); &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;\r\n        error_log(\'MySQL Error: \'.$report);\r\n        die(\'An unexpected database error occured, please ask an admin to check the log files\');\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; }\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-14 09:42:44','2016-09-14 09:42:44',NULL),(228,15,1,'Server Map Diagram','A diagram showing the iaptus servers, their associated modules and databases, and places where communication happens between servers and modules.','<div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"max-width:100%;\" data-mxgraph=\"{&quot;highlight&quot;:&quot;#0000ff&quot;,&quot;nav&quot;:true,&quot;edit&quot;:&quot;_blank&quot;,&quot;xml&quot;:&quot;&lt;mxfile userAgent=\\&quot;Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36\\&quot; version=\\&quot;5.6.0.5\\&quot; editor=\\&quot;www.draw.io\\&quot; type=\\&quot;google\\&quot;&gt;&lt;diagram&gt;&lt;/diagram&gt;&lt;/mxfile&gt;&quot;}\"></div>',1,1,'2016-09-14 10:21:43','2016-09-14 10:21:43',NULL),(229,22,16,'Configuring Test Sites For Self Referral Testing','Setup steps for test sites in order to test Self Referrals','<p>1. Follow <a href=\"http://black-box.mayden.co.uk/p/mayden/servers/deploying-test-sites\">these instructions</a> on setting up a test site</p>\r\n\r\n<p>2. Follow <a href=\"http://black-box.mayden.co.uk/p/mayden/servers/copying-live-data-to-test-sites\">these instructions</a> on copying a live database to the test site</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3. Configure the test site for use with self referrals (datacentre agnostic)</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>On the server containing your chosen iaptus test site, go to&nbsp;<code>/var/www/html/iaptustest-testing-XX/cron_live </code>and in<code> cron_setup.php </code>modify the Postroom URL to point at a testing postroom, e.g.&nbsp;https://postroomtest-a3.iaptus.nhs.uk</li>\r\n	<li>Edit&nbsp;<code>cron-config.php</code> and uncomment the \"<code>CronSelfReferrals</code>\" lines</li>\r\n	<li>On the server containing your test postroom (note, MAY be a different server to where your test site is), go to<code> /var/www/html/postroomtest-xx/cron</code></li>\r\n	<li>Modify <code>postroom_cron_config.php</code> and uncomment the lines regarding \"<code>SelfReferralsMaydenTask</code>\"</li>\r\n	<li>In the test postroom database, (api_testXX) add the service id and the form UUID (see other article) to the service_config table​</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>4. Once the test referral has been submitted, run the following command in the test postroom root folder: \"<code>php public/index.php cron process</code>\". Once run successfully the data will appear in the collection_box table of the database. Re-comment the <code>postroom_cron_config.php</code>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5. Go back to your iaptus test site and go to <code>/var/www/html/iaptustest-testing-XX/cron_live</code> and run: \"<code>php cron.php</code>\". When done, re-comment out the lines in cron config.</p>\r\n',1,29,'2016-09-14 10:21:55','2016-09-14 10:31:11',NULL),(230,13,1,'Server Node Diagram','A diagram showing the setup of iaptus server nodes and access points.','<p>This diagram shows access points for the various iaptus nodes available. External traffic is funnelled to the loadbalances and distributed between nodes as it sees fit. Local traffic (e.g. developers on local machines) is directed by local SSH config settings and provided access via VPN. Depending on your SSH config, you should be able to access all nodes from a single VPN/SSH entry point.</p>\r\n\r\n<div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"max-width:100%;\" data-mxgraph=\"{&quot;highlight&quot;:&quot;#0000ff&quot;,&quot;nav&quot;:true,&quot;edit&quot;:&quot;_blank&quot;,&quot;xml&quot;:&quot;&lt;mxfile userAgent=\\&quot;Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36\\&quot; version=\\&quot;5.6.0.5\\&quot; editor=\\&quot;www.draw.io\\&quot; type=\\&quot;google\\&quot;&gt;&lt;diagram&gt;&lt;/diagram&gt;&lt;/mxfile&gt;&quot;}\"></div>',1,1,'2016-09-14 10:22:20','2016-09-14 10:22:20',NULL),(231,14,4,'Sensu Process Diagram','A diagram showing the process Mayden use to operate Sensu monitoring.','<div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"max-width:100%;\" data-mxgraph=\"{&quot;highlight&quot;:&quot;#0000ff&quot;,&quot;nav&quot;:true,&quot;edit&quot;:&quot;_blank&quot;,&quot;xml&quot;:&quot;&lt;mxfile userAgent=\\&quot;Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36\\&quot; version=\\&quot;5.6.0.5\\&quot; editor=\\&quot;www.draw.io\\&quot; type=\\&quot;google\\&quot;&gt;&lt;diagram&gt;&lt;/diagram&gt;&lt;/mxfile&gt;&quot;}\"></div>',1,1,'2016-09-14 10:23:02','2016-09-14 10:23:02',NULL),(232,10,3,'\"What Kind of Test Should I Write?\"','A flow diagram to help you make a decision as to what kind of automated test to write to test a certain piece of code.','<div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"max-width:100%;\" data-mxgraph=\"{&quot;highlight&quot;:&quot;#0000ff&quot;,&quot;nav&quot;:true,&quot;edit&quot;:&quot;_blank&quot;,&quot;xml&quot;:&quot;&lt;mxfile userAgent=\\&quot;Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36\\&quot; version=\\&quot;5.6.0.5\\&quot; editor=\\&quot;www.draw.io\\&quot; type=\\&quot;google\\&quot;&gt;&lt;diagram&gt;&lt;/diagram&gt;&lt;/mxfile&gt;&quot;}\"></div>',1,1,'2016-09-14 10:23:31','2016-09-14 10:23:31',NULL),(233,12,13,'Webform Process Diagram','A diagram showing how Webforms are used with iaptus, including how they make their way from iaptus to the patient and back again.','<div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"max-width:100%;\" data-mxgraph=\"{&quot;highlight&quot;:&quot;#0000ff&quot;,&quot;nav&quot;:true,&quot;edit&quot;:&quot;_blank&quot;,&quot;xml&quot;:&quot;&lt;mxfile userAgent=\\&quot;Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36\\&quot; version=\\&quot;5.6.0.5\\&quot; editor=\\&quot;www.draw.io\\&quot; type=\\&quot;google\\&quot;&gt;&lt;diagram&gt;&lt;/diagram&gt;&lt;/mxfile&gt;&quot;}\"></div>',1,1,'2016-09-14 10:24:03','2016-09-14 10:24:03',NULL),(234,12,13,'Webform Process Diagram','A diagram showing how Webforms are used with iaptus, including how they make their way from iaptus to the patient and back again.','<div class=\"mxgraph\" style=\"max-width:100%;\" data-mxgraph=\"{&quot;highlight&quot;:&quot;#f4f6fa&quot;,&quot;nav&quot;:true,&quot;edit&quot;:&quot;_blank&quot;,&quot;xml&quot;:&quot;&lt;mxfile userAgent=\\&quot;Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; WOW64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/52.0.2743.116 Safari/537.36\\&quot; version=\\&quot;5.6.0.5\\&quot; editor=\\&quot;www.draw.io\\&quot; type=\\&quot;google\\&quot;&gt;&lt;diagram&gt;&lt;/diagram&gt;&lt;/mxfile&gt;&quot;}\"></div>',1,1,'2016-09-14 10:25:48','2016-09-14 10:25:48',NULL),(235,48,29,'Manually Removing Care Pathway Links','How to remove a link from a care pathway so it no longer appears on the care pathway tools','<p>Where care pathway diagrams are too large to load in the care pathway diagram tool, it may be necessary manually remove links from care pathways. This must be done on the Demo site and the link itself must <strong>not&nbsp;</strong>be deleted - only archived/\'olded\'.&nbsp;To do so, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>To start, you will need the IDs of the care pathway stages for which the link needs deleting. You should locate the stages in the nh_stage table for which the link between needs to be removed, making note of the ID for the \'from\' stage (where the patient would start out) and the ID for the \'to\' stage (where the patient could progress to). Make sure you have selected the stage for the correct service using the ser_id column.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Next, use these IDs to find the link in the nh_stage_process table and change the live column from <code>1</code> to <code>0</code>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>UPDATE nh_stage_process SET live=0 WHERE stage_from=STAGE_FROM_ID AND stage_to=STAGE_TO_ID;</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you need to set the link in the XML to archived too. You can find the XML in the&nbsp;nh_diagram table. Open the XML in a text editor and locate&nbsp;the link which needs archiving. You will be able to find it by removing the service id and \'00\' from the beginning of the STAGE_FROM&nbsp;ID and&nbsp;STAGE_TO_ID and looking for the link with a source and target with this number in it. For example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>SERVICE_ID = 160</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>STAGE_FROM_ID = 1600022</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>STAGE_TO_ID = 1600044</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To archive the link, simply replace the <code>hidden=&quot;0&quot;&amp;nbsp;archived=&quot;0&quot;</code> part with&nbsp;<code>hidden=&quot;1&quot;&amp;nbsp;archived=&quot;1&quot;:</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you need to check that it is no longer possible travel between the two stages in the Care Pathway section on iaptus. When you have a patient in the \'stage from\' stage, it should not be possible to process the patient onto the \'to stage\' as you removed the link.</p>\r\n',1,35,'2016-09-20 15:49:57','2016-09-21 13:28:29',NULL),(236,61,8,'Prism Database Tables','Describes tables used by Prism in iaptus and Postroom','<p>A description of the tables used by Prism in iaptus and the Postroom.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<table border=\"1\" bordercolor=\"#ccc\" cellpadding=\"5\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:1000px\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td><strong>Table Name</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Codebase</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Database</strong></td>\r\n			<td><strong>Description</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>atlas_clinical_contact</td>\r\n			<td>Postroom</td>\r\n			<td>apiv2</td>\r\n			<td>Contains clinical contact data returned from online provider.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>atlas_episode</td>\r\n			<td>Postroom</td>\r\n			<td>apiv2</td>\r\n			<td>Maps episode IDs to external patient UUIDs, episode UUIDs and therapist UUIDs.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>atlas_clinical_contact_link</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>Links a clinical contact ID with an atlas clinical contact ID from postroom (atlas_clinical_contact).</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>online_providers_field_config</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>Field configurations for data to send to online providers (providers have different requirements).</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>online_providers_field_history</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>History of changes made to Prism field configurations, and who made the change.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>online_providers_sent_referrals</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>Details about episodes that have been sent off to third party online provider.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>online_providers_service</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>Links an online provider to an iaptus service. &nbsp;Interface for this is in left hand superuser menu in iaptus, under \"Online Providers\" menu option.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>online_providers</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus_shared</td>\r\n			<td>Master list of all online providers and the flag to indicate whether a provider supports courses</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>online_providers_courses</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus_shared</td>\r\n			<td>List of courses for each online provider - this is just a name and course_id which we send to the online provider to indicate which course the patient is being referred to</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>online_providers_field</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus_shared</td>\r\n			<td>Master list of all fields used for&nbsp;Prism referrals - essentially just a mapping between the name in the JSON data and a display name for the front end</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>online_providers_field_required</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus</td>\r\n			<td>iaptus_shared</td>\r\n			<td>List of fields that each provider&nbsp;<strong>requires</strong> is sent to them in a referral</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,10,'2016-09-21 10:15:17','2016-09-21 13:27:55',NULL),(237,54,17,'Copy New Service From Demo DB to Live DB','Information about the tools folder scripts that are used when copying the relevant data for a new service from the demo database (which has all services) to a live database (with just the data for the new service which is going live). (For information about the Dev-Ops system team work in setting up a new database on the live server and registering the new domain etc see Dev-Ops->iaptus->Setup new IAPTus live sites.)','<p><em>NOTE - the script discussed in this article is a legacy script that has been proposed for refactoring. The following explanation is correct at the time of writing in August 2016.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Create New Single Service Database to go Live</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>When a client has approved their demo site developers need to get the relevant data from the demo database for that service and create an iaptus single service live database to be copied to the live server</strong>. Relevant entries for the global database relating to the new service also need to be run on the live global databases. This is all done using scripts located in <code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools</code> folder that are run locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Running the copy demo to live script</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Export whole iaptus demo database from the demo server&nbsp;as mysqldump and then import locally to Vagrant box.</li>\r\n	<li>Rename local copy demo database to \"<code>iaptus_demo_bak&quot;.</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new empty local database called&nbsp; \"<code>iaptus_new_client&quot;</code></li>\r\n	<li>Checkout up to date copy of the iaptus codebase (master) and go to the file at <code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data_example.inc</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new file&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data.inc</code> by copying db_data_example.inc</li>\r\n	<li>Edit the db_data_example.inc file so that it contains valid database&nbsp;details to create the $dbDemoBak and $dbNewClient connections to local databases iaptus_demo_bak and iaptus_new_client (see above)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to&nbsp;file at&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/inc/setup_example.php</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new file&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/inc/setup.php</code>&nbsp;by copying setup_example.php</li>\r\n	<li>Edit setup.php so that it looks like setup.php below</li>\r\n	<li>In your browser go to your vagrant iaptus URL and append the path to the following file: iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/new_client.php. You should see a page of links to various New Client Setup tools.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the link labelled 2. New Client Setup. You should then get choices at the bottom. Check target and source databases, choose IAPT or&nbsp;CYP as appropriate and choose the appropriate service from the drop down list. Click Setup button. The database script should then put all the appropriate data into the iaptus_new_client database and you should also be given some SQL insert statements to be run on the Global iaptus databases for service specific entries from the demo global database tables.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>setup.php</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/includes/iaptusdevelopment/db_data_old_style.inc\');\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data.inc\');\r\ndefine(\'SCORING_CLASS_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/html/forms/scoring/\');\r\ndefine(\'MYSQL_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/tools/importTool/mysql/\');\r\ndefine(\'IAPTUS_PATH\', \'/iaptus/trunk/html\');\r\nfunction checkDBError(&amp;amp;$DBObject)\r\n{\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; if (PEAR::isError($DBObject))\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; {\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; $trace=debug_backtrace();\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; $report=str_replace(\'/var/www/html/\', \'\', $trace[0][\'file\']).\' Line: \'.$trace[0][\'line\'].\' Msg: \'.$DBObject---&amp;gt;getDebugInfo(); &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;\r\n        error_log(\'MySQL Error: \'.$report);\r\n        die(\'An unexpected database error occured, please ask an admin to check the log files\');\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; }\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>db_date.inc</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&lt;?php<br />\r\nrequire_once(\"DB.php\");</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$hostname &nbsp;= \"192.168.20.56\";<br />\r\n$username &nbsp;= \"root\";<br />\r\n$password &nbsp;= \"\";<br />\r\n$database &nbsp; = \"iaptus_demo_bak\";</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$dbDemoBak = DB::connect(\"mysql://$username:$password@$hostname/$database\");<br />\r\nif(DB::isError($dbDemoBak))<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; die($dbDemoBak-&gt;getMessage());<br />\r\n$dbDemoBak-&gt;setFetchMode (DB_FETCHMODE_ASSOC);</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$hostname &nbsp;= \"192.168.20.56\";<br />\r\n$username &nbsp;= \"root\";<br />\r\n$password &nbsp;= \"\";<br />\r\n$database &nbsp; = \"iaptus_new_client&quot;;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>$dbNewClient = DB::connect(\"mysql://$username:$password@$hostname/$database\");<br />\r\nif(DB::isError($dbNewClient))<br />\r\n&nbsp; &nbsp; die($dbNewClient-&gt;getMessage());<br />\r\n$dbNewClient-&gt;setFetchMode (DB_FETCHMODE_ASSOC);</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n?&gt;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,36,'2016-09-21 12:59:20','2016-09-21 13:21:45',NULL),(238,54,17,'Copy New Service From Demo DB to Live DB','Information about the tools folder scripts that are used when copying the relevant data for a new service from the demo database (which has all services) to a live database (with just the data for the new service which is going live). (For information about the Dev-Ops system team work in setting up a new database on the live server and registering the new domain etc see Dev-Ops->iaptus->Setup new IAPTus live sites.)','<p><em>NOTE - the script discussed in this article is a legacy script that has been proposed for refactoring. The following explanation is correct at the time of writing in August 2016.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Create New Single Service Database to go Live</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>When a client has approved their demo site developers need to get the relevant data from the demo database for that service and create an iaptus single service live database to be copied to the live server</strong>. Relevant entries for the global database relating to the new service also need to be run on the live global databases. This is all done using scripts located in <code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools</code> folder that are run locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Running the copy demo to live script</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Export whole iaptus demo database from the demo server&nbsp;as mysqldump and then import locally to Vagrant box. However export nh_stats, nh_stats_history, nh_stats_speed, nh_diagram, nh_stage_xml,&nbsp;nh_user_activity_edit and&nbsp;nh_user_activity_view as empty tables, otherwise you will be copying alot of data.</li>\r\n	<li>Rename local copy demo database to \"<code>iaptus_demo_bak&quot;.</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new empty local database called&nbsp; \"<code>iaptus_new_client&quot;</code></li>\r\n	<li>Checkout up to date copy of the iaptus codebase (master) and go to the file at <code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data_example.inc</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new file&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data.inc</code> by copying db_data_example.inc</li>\r\n	<li>Edit the db_data_example.inc file so that it contains valid database&nbsp;details to create the $dbDemoBak and $dbNewClient connections to local databases iaptus_demo_bak and iaptus_new_client (see above)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to&nbsp;file at&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/inc/setup_example.php</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new file&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/inc/setup.php</code>&nbsp;by copying setup_example.php</li>\r\n	<li>Edit setup.php so that it looks like setup.php below</li>\r\n	<li>In your browser go to your vagrant iaptus URL and append the path to the following file: iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/new_client.php. You should see a page of links to various New Client Setup tools.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the link labelled 2. New Client Setup. You should then get choices at the bottom. Check target and source databases, choose IAPT or&nbsp;CYP as appropriate and choose the appropriate service from the drop down list. Click Setup button. The database script should then put all the appropriate data into the iaptus_new_client database and you should also be given some SQL insert statements to be run on the Global iaptus databases for service specific entries from the demo global database tables.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>setup.php</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n&amp;lt;?php\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/includes/iaptusdevelopment/db_data_old_style.inc\');\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data.inc\');\r\ndefine(\'SCORING_CLASS_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/html/forms/scoring/\');\r\ndefine(\'MYSQL_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/tools/importTool/mysql/\');\r\nfunction checkDBError(&amp;amp;$DBObject)\r\n{\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; if (PEAR::isError($DBObject))\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; {\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; $trace=debug_backtrace();\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; $report=str_replace(\'/var/www/html/\', \'\', $trace[0][\'file\']).\' Line: \'.$trace[0][\'line\'].\' Msg: \'.$DBObject---&amp;gt;getDebugInfo(); &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;\r\n        error_log(\'MySQL Error: \'.$report);\r\n        die(\'An unexpected database error occured, please ask an admin to check the log files\');\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; }\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>db_date.inc</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n&amp;lt;?php\r\nrequire_once(&quot;DB.php&quot;);\r\n\r\n$hostname  = &quot;192.168.20.56&quot;;\r\n$username  = &quot;root&quot;;\r\n$password  = &quot;&quot;;\r\n$database   = &quot;iaptus_demo_bak&quot;;\r\n\r\n$dbDemoBak = DB::connect(&quot;mysql://$username:$password@$hostname/$database&quot;);\r\nif(DB::isError($dbDemoBak))\r\n    die($dbDemoBak-&amp;gt;getMessage());\r\n$dbDemoBak-&amp;gt;setFetchMode (DB_FETCHMODE_ASSOC);\r\n\r\n$hostname  = &quot;192.168.20.56&quot;;\r\n$username  = &quot;root&quot;;\r\n$password  = &quot;&quot;;\r\n$database   = &quot;iaptus_new_client&amp;quot;;\r\n\r\n$dbNewClient = DB::connect(&quot;mysql://$username:$password@$hostname/$database&quot;);\r\nif(DB::isError($dbNewClient))\r\n    die($dbNewClient-&amp;gt;getMessage());\r\n$dbNewClient-&amp;gt;setFetchMode (DB_FETCHMODE_ASSOC);\r\n</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,36,'2016-09-21 13:07:12','2016-09-21 13:27:03',NULL),(239,62,18,'Tidy up mqueue on maydenmtanode16','This is how you can tidy up the mqueue, as it will have a lot of email that has not been sent. The main issue is email destined for maydenasvnode1/2/3/5 or similar, this does need addressing.','<p>Follow the following steps to remove any unsent emails on asvnodes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>login to maydenmtanode16</li>\r\n	<li><code>cd /var/spool/mqueue</code></li>\r\n	<li><code>sudo sh /root/del_mail</code></li>\r\n	<li><code>sudo sh /root/tmp</code></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 13:21:19','2016-09-21 13:21:19',NULL),(240,54,17,'Co