ne on the Demo site and the link itself must <strong>not&nbsp;</strong>be deleted - only archived/\'olded\'.&nbsp;To do so, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p>To start, you will need the IDs of the care pathway stages for which the link needs deleting. You should locate the stages in the nh_stage table for which the link between needs to be removed, making note of the ID for the \'from\' stage (where the patient would start out) and the ID for the \'to\' stage (where the patient could progress to). Make sure you have selected the stage for the correct service using the ser_id column.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Next, use these IDs to find the link in the nh_stage_process table and change the live column from <code>1</code> to <code>0</code>:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>UPDATE nh_stage_process SET live=0 WHERE stage_from=STAGE_FROM_ID AND stage_to=STAGE_TO_ID;</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you need to set the link in the XML to archived too. You can find the XML in the&nbsp;nh_diagram table. Open the XML in a text editor and locate&nbsp;the link which needs archiving. You will be able to find it by removing the service id and \'00\' from the beginning of the STAGE_FROM&nbsp;ID and&nbsp;STAGE_TO_ID and looking for the link with a source and target with this number in it. For example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>SERVICE_ID = 160</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>STAGE_FROM_ID = 1600022</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p><code>STAGE_TO_ID = 1600044</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To archive the link, simply replace the <code>hidden=&quot;0&quot; archived=&quot;0&quot;</code> part with&nbsp;<code>hidden=&quot;1&quot; archived=&quot;1&quot;:</code></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Finally, you need to check that it is no longer possible travel between the two stages in the Care Pathway section on iaptus. When you have a patient in the \'stage from\' stage, it should not be possible to process the patient onto the \'to stage\' as you removed the link.</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 13:28:48','2016-09-21 13:28:48',NULL),(245,62,18,'Tidy Mqueue On Maydenmtanode16','This is how you can tidy up the mqueue, as it will have a lot of email that has not been sent. The main issue is email destined for maydenasvnode1/2/3/5 or similar, this does need addressing.','<p>Follow the following steps to remove any unsent emails on asvnodes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>login to maydenmtanode16</li>\r\n	<li><code>cd /var/spool/mqueue</code></li>\r\n	<li><code>sudo sh /root/del_mail</code></li>\r\n	<li><code>sudo sh /root/tmp</code></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 13:34:58','2016-09-21 13:34:58',NULL),(246,77,29,'Setting Care Pathway Diagram Locally','How to import a care pathway from demo into your local version of iaptus.','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>In your local iaptus database truncate the nh_stage and nh_stage_process tables</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Copy the row for the diagram you need&nbsp;in Demo\'s&nbsp;nh_diagram table</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Insert this row into nh_diagram table into your local iaptus database, remembering to change the ser_id column value to 101</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click the “New Care Pathway Tool” superuser link in your local version of iaptus</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Select&nbsp;the diagram you have just inserted into the database</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Click “Export To Demo Site”. This will populate rows in nh_stage and nh_stage_process tables and you will be able to see this care pathway in “Care Pathway (Mayden Only)” tool</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 13:40:00','2016-09-21 13:40:00',NULL),(247,77,29,'Setting Care Pathway Diagram Locally','How to import a care pathway from demo into your local version of iaptus.','<p>To&nbsp;import a care pathway from demo into your local version of iaptus, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>In your local iaptus database truncate the nh_stage and nh_stage_process tables</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Copy the row for the diagram you need&nbsp;in Demo\'s&nbsp;nh_diagram table</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Insert this row into nh_diagram table into your local iaptus database, remembering to change the ser_id column value to 101</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click the “New Care Pathway Tool” superuser link in your local version of iaptus</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Select&nbsp;the diagram you have just inserted into the database</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Click “Export To Demo Site”. This will populate rows in nh_stage and nh_stage_process tables and you will be able to see this care pathway in “Care Pathway (Mayden Only)” tool</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 13:40:20','2016-09-21 13:40:20',NULL),(248,77,29,'Importing a Care Pathway Diagram Locally','How to import a care pathway from demo into your local version of iaptus.','<p>To&nbsp;import a care pathway from demo into your local version of iaptus, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>In your local iaptus database truncate the nh_stage and nh_stage_process tables</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Copy the row for the diagram you need&nbsp;in Demo\'s&nbsp;nh_diagram table</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Insert this row into nh_diagram table into your local iaptus database, remembering to change the ser_id column value to 101</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click the “New Care Pathway Tool” superuser link in your local version of iaptus</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Select&nbsp;the diagram you have just inserted into the database</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Click “Export To Demo Site”. This will populate rows in nh_stage and nh_stage_process tables and you will be able to see this care pathway in “Care Pathway (Mayden Only)” tool</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 13:41:06','2016-09-21 13:41:06',NULL),(249,78,29,'Download Care Pathway PDF','How to download a copy of a care pathway diagram PDF','<p>To download a copy of a care pathway diagram PDF, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Go to “New Care Pathway Tool” in <strong>iaptus</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Open the&nbsp;last&nbsp;non-autosaved&nbsp;diagram.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Wait for it to load (it might take some time)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Click “Create PDF” - this should trigger download.If it does&nbsp;not, check your pop-up settings.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Attach the&nbsp;downloaded PDF to the relevant orbit task, if necessary</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 13:53:40','2016-09-21 13:53:40',NULL),(250,79,29,'Updating Care Pathway Diagram On Demo','to be updated','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make the necessary changes in the care pathway xml</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write a patch with the following queries:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li class=\"no-bullet\">\r\n		    <pre>\r\n                 DELETE FROM nh_stage WHERE ser_id=SER_ID_HERE\r\n                 DELETE FROM nh_stage_process WHERE pathway_id=SER_ID_HERE\r\n            </pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Insert row in nh_diagram table in demo database with corrected diagram</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>INSERT INTO `nh_diagram` (`ser_id`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`title`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`author`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`date`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`xml`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`notes`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`autosave`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`imported`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`live`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`removed`)<br />\r\nVALUES (#service id here#,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'#Service name here#\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'#Your initials here#\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;‘#XML here#’,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'#notes here#\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'1\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'0\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'0\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'0\'<br />\r\n);</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the notes please include what has changed / what has been fixed and add the note that it has been exported to demo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This queries will have to be run manually on demo database. Please, ask someone from release team to code review it before you will run it. In JIRA in the “Special Notes for Release Team”, please put “Please do not run on live, patch already has been run manually on demo database.”. After queries are run, please make sure that you complete the JIRA workflow and get this issue into release branch and to “deployed” stage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Go to “New Care Pathway Tool” in demo site for this service, open your diagram and click “Export To Demo Site”. This will populate rows in nh_stage and nh_stage_process tables and you will be able to see this care pathway in “Care Pathway (Mayden Only)” tool.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 13:58:05','2016-09-21 13:58:05',NULL),(251,79,29,'Updating Care Pathway Diagram On Demo','to be updated','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make the necessary changes in the care pathway xml</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write a patch with the following queries:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nDELETE FROM nh_stage WHERE ser_id=SER_ID_HERE\r\nDELETE FROM nh_stage_process WHERE pathway_id=SER_ID_HERE\r\n            </pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Insert row in nh_diagram table in demo database with corrected diagram</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>INSERT INTO `nh_diagram` (`ser_id`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`title`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`author`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`date`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`xml`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`notes`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`autosave`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`imported`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`live`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`removed`)<br />\r\nVALUES (#service id here#,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'#Service name here#\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'#Your initials here#\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;‘#XML here#’,</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'#notes here#\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'1\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'0\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'0\',<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\'0\'<br />\r\n);</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the notes please include what has changed / what has been fixed and add the note that it has been exported to demo.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This queries will have to be run manually on demo database. Please, ask someone from release team to code review it before you will run it. In JIRA in the “Special Notes for Release Team”, please put “Please do not run on live, patch already has been run manually on demo database.”. After queries are run, please make sure that you complete the JIRA workflow and get this issue into release branch and to “deployed” stage.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Go to “New Care Pathway Tool” in demo site for this service, open your diagram and click “Export To Demo Site”. This will populate rows in nh_stage and nh_stage_process tables and you will be able to see this care pathway in “Care Pathway (Mayden Only)” tool.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 13:58:20','2016-09-21 13:58:20',NULL),(252,79,29,'Updating Care Pathway Diagram On Demo','to be updated','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make the necessary changes in the care pathway xml</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write a patch with the following queries:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>DELETE FROM nh_stage WHERE ser_id=SER_ID_HERE\r\nDELETE FROM nh_stage_process WHERE pathway_id=SER_ID_HERE</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<p>Insert row in nh_diagram table in demo database with corrected diagram</p>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>Example:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>INSERT INTO `nh_diagram` (`ser_id`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`title`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`author`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`date`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`xml`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`notes`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`autosave`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;`imported`,<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n