09-21 14:06:12','2016-09-21 14:06:12',NULL),(256,79,29,'Changing a Care Pathway On Demo','How to get manual changes to a care pathway put onto demo','<ol>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Make the necessary changes in the care pathway xml</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write a patch with the following queries:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nDELETE FROM nh_stage WHERE ser_id=SER_ID_HERE\r\nDELETE FROM nh_stage_process WHERE pathway_id=SER_ID_HERE</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Write a patch which inserts a row into the nh_diagram table in the demo database with corrected diagram xml, for example:</p>\r\n\r\n	<ol>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nINSERT INTO `nh_diagram` (\r\n    `ser_id`,\r\n    `title`,\r\n    `author`,\r\n    `date`,\r\n    `xml`,\r\n    `notes`,\r\n    `autosave`,\r\n    `imported`,\r\n    `live`,\r\n    `removed`\r\n) VALUES (\r\n    SERVICE_ID_HERE,\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;SERVICE_NAME_HERE,\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;YOUR_INITIALS_HERE,\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;CURRENT_TIMESTAMP,\r\n    XML_HERE,\r\n    NOTES_HERE\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;\'1\',\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;\'0\',\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;\'0\',\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;\'0\'\r\n);</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ol>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>In the notes please include what has changed / what has been fixed and add the note that it has been exported to demo.</li>\r\n	<li>These queries will have to be run manually on demo database. Please ask someone from release team to code review it before you run it. Update the “Special Notes for Release Team” section in JIRA with \"Please do not run on live, patch already has been run manually on demo database.”. After the queries have been run, please make sure that you complete the JIRA workflow and get this issue into release branch and to “deployed” stage.</li>\r\n	<li>Go to “New Care Pathway Tool” in demo site for this service, open your diagram and click “Export To Demo Site”. This will populate rows in nh_stage and nh_stage_process tables and you will be able to see this care pathway in “Care Pathway (Mayden Only)” tool.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 14:07:08','2016-09-21 14:07:08',NULL),(257,81,29,'Find Patient From','to be updated','<p>To make a care pathway stage appear&nbsp;in&nbsp;the \'Find Patients From\' sidebar&nbsp;area you need to write a patch which sets the value of the <code>stage_shotcut </code>column to “yes” in the nh_stage table for that stage. To remove a care pathway stage from&nbsp;the \'Find Patients From\' sidebar&nbsp;area, set the column value to \"no\"&nbsp;instead.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Example patch text:</h3>\r\n<pre>UPDATE nh_stage\r\nSET stage_shotcut = \'yes\'\r\nWHERE ser_id = 101\r\nAND `id` IN(71, 118, 295, 321);</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 14:10:33','2016-09-21 14:10:33',NULL),(258,81,29,'Adding Stages to \'Find Patients From\'','How to add a care pathway stage to the \'Find Patients From\' sidebar area','<p>To make a care pathway stage appear&nbsp;in&nbsp;the \'Find Patients From\' sidebar&nbsp;area you need to write a patch which sets the value of the <code>stage_shotcut </code>column to “yes” in the nh_stage table for that stage. To remove a care pathway stage from&nbsp;the \'Find Patients From\' sidebar&nbsp;area, set the column value to \"no\"&nbsp;instead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Example patch text:</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nUPDATE nh_stage\r\nSET stage_shotcut = \'yes\'\r\nWHERE ser_id = 101\r\nAND `id` IN(71, 118, 295, 321);</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 14:11:42','2016-09-21 14:11:42',NULL),(259,81,29,'Adding Stages to \'Find Patients From\'','How to add a care pathway stage to the \'Find Patients From\' sidebar area','<p>To make a care pathway stage appear&nbsp;in&nbsp;the \'Find Patients From\' sidebar&nbsp;area you need to write a patch which sets the value of the <code>stage_shotcut</code> column to “yes” in the nh_stage table for that stage. To remove a care pathway stage from&nbsp;the \'Find Patients From\' sidebar&nbsp;area, set the column value to \"no\"&nbsp;instead.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Example patch text:</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nUPDATE nh_stage\r\nSET stage_shotcut = \'yes\'\r\nWHERE ser_id = 101\r\nAND `id` IN(71, 118, 295, 321);</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 14:12:21','2016-09-21 14:12:21',NULL),(260,54,17,'Putting a New Demo Service Live','Information about the tools folder scripts that are used when copying the relevant data for a new service from the demo database (which has all services) to a live database (with just the data for the new service which is going live). (For information about the Dev-Ops system team work in setting up a new database on the live server and registering the new domain etc see Dev-Ops->iaptus->Setup new IAPTus live sites.)','<p><em>NOTE - the script discussed in this article is a legacy script that has been proposed for refactoring. The following explanation is correct at the time of writing in August 2016.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Create New Single Service Database to go Live</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>When a client has approved their demo site developers need to get the relevant data from the demo database for that service and create an iaptus single service live database to be copied to the live server</strong>. Relevant entries for the global database relating to the new service also need to be run on the live global databases. This is all done using scripts located in <code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools</code> folder that are run locally.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Running the copy demo to live script</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Export whole iaptus demo database from the demo server&nbsp;as mysqldump and then import locally to Vagrant box.&nbsp;However export nh_stats, nh_stats_history, nh_stats_speed, nh_diagram, nh_stage_xml,&nbsp;nh_user_activity_edit and&nbsp;nh_user_activity_view as empty tables, otherwise you will be copying alot of data.</li>\r\n	<li>Rename local copy demo database to \"<code>iaptus_demo_bak&quot;.</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new empty local database called&nbsp; \"<code>iaptus_new_client&quot;</code></li>\r\n	<li>Checkout up to date copy of the iaptus codebase (master) and go to the file at <code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data_example.inc</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new file&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data.inc</code> by copying db_data_example.inc</li>\r\n	<li>Edit the db_data_example.inc file so that it contains valid database&nbsp;details to create the $dbDemoBak and $dbNewClient connections to local databases iaptus_demo_bak and iaptus_new_client (see above)</li>\r\n	<li>Go to&nbsp;file at&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/inc/setup_example.php</code></li>\r\n	<li>Create new file&nbsp;<code>iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/inc/setup.php</code>&nbsp;by copying setup_example.php</li>\r\n	<li>Edit setup.php so that it looks like setup.php below</li>\r\n	<li>In your browser go to your vagrant iaptus URL and append the path to the following file: iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/new_client.php. You should see a page of links to various New Client Setup tools.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the link labelled 2. New Client Setup. You should then get choices at the bottom. Check target and source databases, choose IAPT or&nbsp;CYP as appropriate and choose the appropriate service from the drop down list. Click Setup button. The database script should then put all the appropriate data into the iaptus_new_client database and you should also be given some SQL insert statements to be run on the Global iaptus databases for service specific entries from the demo global database tables.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>setup.php:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/includes/iaptusdevelopment/db_data_old_style.inc\');\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data.inc\');\r\ndefine(\'SCORING_CLASS_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/html/forms/scoring/\');\r\ndefine(\'MYSQL_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/tools/importTool/mysql/\');\r\ndefine(\'IAPTUS_PATH\', \'/iaptus/trunk/html\');\r\nfunction checkDBError(&amp;amp;$DBObject)\r\n{\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;if (PEAR::isError($DBObject)) {\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;$trace=debug_backtrace();\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;$report=str_replace(\'/var/www/html/\', \'\', $trace[0][\'file\']).\' Line: \'.$trace[0][\'line\'].\' Msg: \'.$DBObject---&amp;gt;getDebugInfo();\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;error_log(\'MySQL Error: \'.$report);\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;die(\'An unexpected database error occured, please ask an admin to check the log files\');\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>db_data.inc:</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n$hostname &amp;nbsp;= &quot;192.168.20.56&quot;;\r\n$username &amp;nbsp;= &quot;root&quot;;\r\n$password &amp;nbsp;= &quot;&quot;;\r\n$database &amp;nbsp; = &quot;iaptus_demo_bak&quot;;\r\n\r\n$dbDemoBak = DB::connect(&quot;mysql://$username:$password@$hostname/$database&quot;);\r\nif(DB::isError($dbDemoBak))\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; die($dbDemoBak-&amp;gt;getMessage());\r\n$dbDemoBak-&amp;gt;setFetchMode (DB_FETCHMODE_ASSOC);\r\n\r\n$hostname &amp;nbsp;= &quot;192.168.20.56&quot;;\r\n$username &amp;nbsp;= &quot;root&quot;;\r\n$password &amp;nbsp;= &quot;&quot;;\r\n$database &amp;nbsp; = &quot;iaptus_new_client&amp;quot;;\r\n\r\n$dbNewClient = DB::connect(&quot;mysql://$username:$password@$hostname/$database&quot;);\r\nif(DB::isError($dbNewClient))\r\ndie($dbNewClient-&amp;gt;getMessage());\r\n$dbNewClient-&amp;gt;setFetchMode (DB_FETCHMODE_ASSOC);\r\n</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 14:32:48','2016-09-21 14:32:48',NULL),(261,54,17,'Putting a New Demo Service Live','Information about the tools folder