up_example.php</li>\r\n	<li>Edit setup.php so that it looks like setup.php below</li>\r\n	<li>In your browser go to your vagrant iaptus URL and append the path to the following file: iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/html/new_client.php. You should see a page of links to various New Client Setup tools.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the link labelled 2. New Client Setup. You should then get choices at the bottom. Check target and source databases, choose IAPT or&nbsp;CYP as appropriate and choose the appropriate service from the drop down list. Click Setup button. The database script should then put all the appropriate data into the iaptus_new_client database and you should also be given some SQL insert statements to be run on the Global iaptus databases for service specific entries from the demo global database tables.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Adding a Documents Folder</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>FTP into the relevant&nbsp;server and navigate to the <code>/var/www/html/iaptus/documents </code>directory</li>\r\n	<li>Create a new directory called \'documentService\' followed by the service id, eg. documentService200</li>\r\n	<li>Create two directories inside this new directory named <code>letters </code>and <code>exports</code></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Add Service to Config File</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>SSH into the server and navigate to <code>/var/www/html/iaptus-deploy-b/html/inc/config</code>&nbsp;for Bournemouth, or&nbsp;<code>/var/www/html/iaptus-deploy/html/inc/config</code> for Bracknell</li>\r\n	<li>Edit serviceconfig.php and add a new array with the new service details in it, where the key is the name of the service\'s includes folder</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Run the Global Patches</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>SSH into the server and navigate to <code>/var/www/html/iaptus/tools</code></li>\r\n	<li>Run the <code>\'php patches.php\'</code> command and when prompted, choose the global database to run patches for</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Deploy the Code</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>SS