wed by the service id, eg. documentService200</li>\r\n	<li>Create two directories inside this new directory named <code>letters </code>and <code>exports</code></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Add Service to Config File</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>SSH into the server and navigate to <code>/var/www/html/iaptus-deploy-b/html/inc/config</code>&nbsp;for Bournemouth, or&nbsp;<code>/var/www/html/iaptus-deploy/html/inc/config</code> for Bracknell</li>\r\n	<li>Edit serviceconfig.php and add a new array with the new service details in it, where the key is the name of the service\'s includes folder</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Run the Global Patches</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>SSH into the server and navigate to <code>/var/www/html/iaptus/tools</code></li>\r\n	<li>Run the <code>\'php patches.php\'</code> command and when prompted, choose the global database to run patches for</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Deploy the Code</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>SSH into the server and navigate to the <code>/var/www/iaptus/build/live</code></li>\r\n	<li>Run the \'phing deploy-local\' command</li>\r\n	<li>Run the \'phing deploy-cluster\' command</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Clear The Server Cache</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Run the <code>curl 127.0.0.1/clear-cache.php</code> command</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Copy Any Letters from Their Demo Documents</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>SSH into the demo server and navigate to <code>/var/www/html/iaptus_live/documents/documentServiceSERVICE_ID_HERE</code></li>\r\n	<li>Copy all of the JPEGS from this directory and upload them to the service\'s documents/letters&nbsp;directory</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>Transfer Over the Service\'s Demo User Accounts</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>SSH into the server and navigate to <code>/var/www/html/iaptus-deploy-b/tools</code></li>\r\n	<li>Run the <code>php passtool.php</code> command</li>\r\n	<li>When prompted, enter \'C\' for the action and follow the prompts\r\n	<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>Delete Dummy Account Users</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Remove dummy/testing users from the service\'s nh_user table</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3>setup.php:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/includes/iaptusdevelopment/db_data_old_style.inc\');\r\nrequire(\'/var/www/html/iaptus/tools/newClientSetupTools/db_data.inc\');\r\ndefine(\'SCORING_CLASS_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/html/forms/scoring/\');\r\ndefine(\'MYSQL_PATH\', \'/var/www/html/iaptus/iaptus/tools/importTool/mysql/\');\r\ndefine(\'IAPTUS_PATH\', \'/iaptus/trunk/html\');\r\nfunction checkDBError(&amp;amp;$DBObject)\r\n{\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;if (PEAR::isError($DBObject)) {\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;$trace=debug_backtrace();\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;$report=str_replace(\'/var/www/html/\', \'\', $trace[0][\'file\']).\' Line: \'.$trace[0][\'line\'].\' Msg: \'.$DBObject---&amp;gt;getDebugInfo();\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;error_log(\'MySQL Error: \'.$report);\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;die(\'An unexpected database error occured, please ask an admin to check the log files\');\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;}\r\n}</pre>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>db_data.inc:</h3>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\n$hostname &amp;nbsp;= &quot;192.168.20.56&quot;;\r\n$username &amp;nbsp;= &quot;root&quot;;\r\n$password &amp;nbsp;= &quot;&quot;;\r\n$database &amp;nbsp; = &quot;iaptus_demo_bak&quot;;\r\n\r\n$dbDemoBak = DB::connect(&quot;mysql://$username:$password@$hostname/$database&quot;);\r\nif(DB::isError($dbDemoBak))\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; die($dbDemoBak-&amp;gt;getMessage());\r\n$dbDemoBak-&amp;gt;setFetchMode (DB_FETCHMODE_ASSOC);\r\n\r\n$hostname &amp;nbsp;= &quot;192.168.20.56&quot;;\r\n$username &amp;nbsp;= &quot;root&quot;;\r\n$password &amp;nbsp;= &quot;&quot;;\r\n$database &amp;nbsp; = &quot;iaptus_new_client&amp;quot;;\r\n\r\n$dbNewClient = DB::connect(&quot;mysql://$username:$password@$hostname/$database&quot;);\r\nif(DB::isError($dbNewClient))\r\ndie($dbNewClient-&amp;gt;getMessage());\r\n$dbNewClient-&amp;gt;setFetchMode (DB_FETCHMODE_ASSOC);\r\n</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-21 15:25:12','2016-09-21 15:25:12',NULL),(269,5,29,'Putting Care Pathways Live','Instructions for how to transfer a care pathway from demo to a live site','<h3>You will need:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Access to Keepass</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How To</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Log into <a href=\"https://demo.iaptus.co.uk\">https://demo.iaptus.co.uk</a> using \'superuser\' followed by the service needing the care pathway as the username, e.g. <code>superuserhull</code>. You can find the password in Keepass under <code>Projects &amp;gt; IAPTus &amp;gt; Websites &amp;gt; Demo</code>.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the \'Care Pathway (Mayden Only)\' link under the Superuser menu.</li>\r\n	<li>Scroll to the \'Care Pathway Sync Tool\' section of the page, which will be close to the bottom. Ensure that the dropdown says \'LIVE\' and then click \'Export\'.</li>\r\n	<li>Open the downloaded file in a text editor and add the following insert statement to the top, to log the patch running:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\n# Changing \'PATCH_FILENAME_HERE\' to the name you will save this patch under and&amp;nbsp;\'DB_USERNAME_HERE\' to your database username\r\n	INSERT INTO db_patches (filename, startDate, endDate, user, logFile) VALUES (\'PATCH_FILENAME_HERE.sql\', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), \'DB_USERNAME_HERE\', \'\');</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Check the patch file and make sure the value of&nbsp;<strong>id&nbsp;</strong>column in&nbsp;<strong>nh_stage</strong>&nbsp;table and<strong>&nbsp;id, stage_from</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>stage_to</strong>&nbsp;columns in&nbsp;<strong>nh_stage_process</strong>&nbsp;table are always less than&nbsp;<strong>100,000</strong>. Double check that the ser_id values in the patch match the ser_id in the nh_service table of the live database to confirm you have picked up the right care pathway from demo.</li>\r\n	<li>Download the nh_stage_process and nh_stage table from the live customer\'s database. &nbsp;Import them into a local database.</li>\r\n	<li>Run the Care Pathway patch (leaving out the last four queries where tables get dropped and renamed) on your local database server, in the same database as the customer\'s imported tables.</li>\r\n	<li>Run the following query on your local database:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nSELECT * \r\nFROM nh_stage_process\r\nLEFT JOIN nh_stage_process_tempVersion ON nh_stage_process.`id` = nh_stage_process_tempVersion.`id`\r\nWHERE nh_stage_process.stage_from != nh_stage_process_tempVersion.stage_from\r\nOR nh_stage_process.stage_to != nh_stage_process_tempVersion.stage_to</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>If any results are returned, new process IDs that link stage_from and stage_to together no longer hold the same stages as they did on the live site. &nbsp;This will lead to data corruption. &nbsp;If rows are returned DO NOT DEPLOY THE CARE PATHWAY. &nbsp;Instead revert the broken Care Pathway on the demo site to a previously stable version.</li>\r\n	<li>Save the patch in the <code>/mysql/service_patches</code> folder.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Notes:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The patch filename should be the current timestamp with no delimiter, followed by the service name, followed by a brief description of the patch (all separated by dashes), for example:<br />\r\n	<code>20160505-hull-care-pathway-to-go-live.sql</code></li>\r\n	<li>Don\'t forget to make a note on Jira that the patch will need to be run manually</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',0,9,'2016-09-22 10:03:58','2016-09-22 12:01:25',NULL),(270,5,29,'Putting Care Pathways Live','Instructions for how to transfer a care pathway from demo to a live site','<h3>You will need:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Access to Keepass</li>\r\n	<li>Live access (or access to someone with live access).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>How To</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Log into <a href=\"https://demo.iaptus.co.uk\">https://demo.iaptus.co.uk</a> using \'superuser\' followed by the service needing the care pathway as the username, e.g. <code>superuserhull</code>. You can find the password in Keepass under <code>Projects &amp;gt; IAPTus &amp;gt; Websites &amp;gt; Demo</code>.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the \'Care Pathway (Mayden Only)\' link under the Superuser menu.</li>\r\n	<li>Scroll to the \'Care Pathway Sync Tool\' section of the page, which will be close to the bottom. Ensure that the dropdown says \'LIVE\' and then click \'Export\'.</li>\r\n	<li>Open the downloaded file in a text editor and add the following insert statement to the top, to log the patch running:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\n# Changing \'PATCH_FILENAME_HERE\' to the name you will save this patch under and&amp;nbsp;\'DB_USERNAME_HERE\' to your database username\r\n	INSERT INTO db_patches (filename, startDate, endDate, user, logFile) VALUES (\'PATCH_FILENAME_HERE.sql\', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), \'DB_USERNAME_HERE\', \'\');</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Check the patch file and make sure the value of&nbsp;<strong>id&nbsp;</strong>column in&nbsp;<strong>nh_stage</strong>&nbsp;table and<strong>&nbsp;id, stage_from</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>stage_to</strong>&nbsp;columns in&nbsp;<strong>nh_stage_process</strong>&nbsp;table are always less than&nbsp;<strong>100,000</strong>. Double check that the ser_id values in the patch match the ser_id in the nh_service table of the live database to confirm you have picked up the right care pathway from demo.</li>\r\n	<li>Download the nh_stage_process and nh_stage table from the live customer\'s database. &nbsp;Import them into a local database.</li>\r\n	<li>Run the Care Pathway patch (leaving out the last four queries where tables get dropped and renamed) on your local database server, in the same database as the customer\'s imported tables.</li>\r\n	<li>Run the following query on your local database:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nSELECT * \r\nFROM nh_stage_process\r\nLEFT JOIN nh_stage_process_tempVersion ON nh_stage_process.`id` = nh_stage_process_tempVersion.`id`\r\nWHERE nh_stage_process.stage_from != nh_stage_process_tempVersion.stage_from\r\nOR nh_stage_process.stage_to != nh_stage_process_tempVersion.stage_to</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>If any results are returned, new process IDs that link stage_from and stage_to together no longer hold the same stages as they did on the live site. &nbsp;This will lead to data corruption. &nbsp;If rows are returned DO NOT DEPLOY THE CARE PATHWAY. &nbsp;Instead revert the broken Care Pathway on the demo site to a previously stable version.</li>\r\n	<li>Save the patch in the <code>/mysql/service_patches</code> folder.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Notes:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The patch filename should be the current timestamp with no delimiter, followed by the service name, followed by a brief description of the patch (all separated by dashes), for example:<br />\r\n	<code>20160505-hull-care-pathway-to-go-live.sql</code></li>\r\n	<li>Don\'t forget to make a note on Jira that the patch will need to be run manually</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,4,'2016-09-22 10:08:36','2016-09-22 11:59:56',NULL),(271,5,29,'Putting Care Pathways Live','Instructions for how to transfer a care pathway from demo to a live site','<h3>You will need:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Access to Keepass</li>\r\n	<li>Live access (or access to someone with live access).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>How To</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Log into <a href=\"https://demo.iaptus.co.uk\">https://demo.iaptus.co.uk</a> using \'superuser\' followed by the service needing the care pathway as the username, e.g. <code>superuserhull</code>. You can find the password in Keepass under <code>Projects &amp;gt; IAPTus &amp;gt; Websites &amp;gt; Demo</code>.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the \'Care Pathway (Mayden Only)\' link under the Superuser menu.</li>\r\n	<li>Scroll to the \'Care Pathway Sync Tool\' section of the page, which will be close to the bottom. Ensure that the dropdown says \'LIVE\' and then click \'Export\'.</li>\r\n	<li>Open the downloaded file in a text editor and add the following insert statement to the top, to log the patch running:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\n# Changing \'PATCH_FILENAME_HERE\' to the name you will save this patch under and&amp;amp;nbsp;\'DB_USERNAME_HERE\' to your database username\r\nINSERT INTO db_patches (filename, startDate, endDate, user, logFile) VALUES (\'PATCH_FILENAME_HERE.sql\', CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), CURRENT_TIMESTAMP(), \'DB_USERNAME_HERE\', \'\');</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Check the patch file and make sure the value of&nbsp;<strong>id&nbsp;</strong>column in&nbsp;<strong>nh_stage</strong>&nbsp;table and<strong>&nbsp;id, stage_from</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>stage_to</strong>&nbsp;columns in&nbsp;<strong>nh_stage_process</strong>&nbsp;table are always less than&nbsp;<strong>100,000</strong>. Double check that the ser_id values in the patch match the ser_id in the nh_service table of the live database to confirm you have picked up the right care pathway from demo.</li>\r\n	<li>Download the nh_stage_process and nh_stage table from the live customer\'s database. &nbsp;Import them into a local database.</li>\r\n	<li>Run the Care Pathway patch (leaving out the last four queries where tables get dropped and renamed) on your local database server, in the same database as the customer\'s imported tables.</li>\r\n	<li>Run the following query on your local database:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nSELECT * \r\nFROM nh_stage_process\r\nLEFT JOIN nh_stage_process_tempVersion ON nh_stage_process.`id` = nh_stage_process_tempVersion.`id`\r\nWHERE nh_stage_process.stage_from != nh_stage_process_tempVersion.stage_from\r\nOR nh_stage_process.stage_to != nh_stage_process_tempVersion.stage_to</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>If any results are returned, new process IDs that link stage_from and stage_to together no longer hold the same stages as they did on the live site. &nbsp;This will lead to data corruption. &nbsp;If rows are returned DO NOT DEPLOY THE CARE PATHWAY. &nbsp;Instead revert the broken Care Pathway on the demo site to a previously stable version.</li>\r\n	<li>Save the patch in the <code>/mysql/service_patches</code> folder.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Notes:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The patch filename should be the current timestamp with no delimiter, followed by the service name, followed by a brief description of the patch (all separated by dashes), for example:<br />\r\n	<code>20160505-hull-care-pathway-to-go-live.sql</code></li>\r\n	<li>Don\'t forget to make a note on Jira that the patch will need to be run manually</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-22 12:00:41','2016-09-22 12:00:41',NULL),(272,5,29,'Putting Care Pathways Live','Instructions for how to transfer a care pathway from demo to a live site','<h3>You will need:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Access to Keepass</li>\r\n	<li>Live access (or access to someone with live access).</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h3>How To</h3>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Log into <a href=\"https://demo.iaptus.co.uk\">https://demo.iaptus.co.uk</a> using \'superuser\' followed by the service needing the care pathway as the username, e.g. <code>superuserhull</code>. You can find the password in Keepass under <code>Projects &amp;gt; IAPTus &amp;gt; Websites &amp;gt; Demo</code>.</li>\r\n	<li>Click the \'Care Pathway (Mayden Only)\' link under the Superuser menu.</li>\r\n	<li>Scroll to the \'C