from and stage_to together no longer hold the same stages as they did on the live site. &nbsp;This will lead to data corruption. &nbsp;If rows are returned DO NOT DEPLOY THE CARE PATHWAY. &nbsp;Instead revert the broken Care Pathway on the demo site to a previously stable version.</li>\r\n	<li>Save the patch in the <code>/mysql/service_patches</code> folder.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Notes:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>The patch filename should be the current timestamp with no delimiter, followed by the service name, followed by a brief description of the patch (all separated by dashes), for example:<br />\r\n	<code>20160505-hull-care-pathway-to-go-live.sql</code></li>\r\n	<li>Don\'t forget to make a note on Jira that the patch will need to be run manually</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-22 12:01:02','2016-09-22 12:01:02',NULL),(273,64,7,'Adding Columns to Find Patients','How to add columns to the \'Find Patients\' data table','<p>To add columns to the \'Find Patients\' table, follow these steps for <strong>each global database</strong>:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Open the nh_searchFields table in the selected global database and find the jsonName of the field you wish to turn on</li>\r\n	<li>Write a global&nbsp;patch which inserts this field into the nh_serSearchFields for the service you who needs this field:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nINSERT INTO nh_serSearchFields (`fieldId`, `ser_id`, `order`) VALUES (\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;(SELECT fieldId FROM nh_searchFields WHERE jsonName=\'JSON_NAME_HERE\' LIMIT 1),&amp;nbsp;\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; SERVICE_ID_HERE,\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 100\r\n);</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-22 12:19:22','2016-09-22 12:19:22',NULL),(274,64,7,'Adding Columns to Find Patients','How to add columns to the \'Find Patients\' data table','<p>To add columns to the \'Find Patients\' table, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Open the nh_searchFields table in the selected global database and find the jsonName of the field you wish to turn on</li>\r\n	<li>Write a global&nbsp;patch which inserts this field into the nh_serSearchFields for the service you who needs this field:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nINSERT INTO nh_serSearchFields (`fieldId`, `ser_id`, `order`) VALUES (\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;(SELECT fieldId FROM nh_searchFields WHERE jsonName=\'JSON_NAME_HERE\' LIMIT 1),&amp;nbsp;\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; SERVICE_ID_HERE,\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 100\r\n);</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-22 12:19:41','2016-09-22 12:19:41',NULL),(275,64,7,'Adding Columns to Find Patients','How to add columns to the \'Find Patients\' data table','<p>To add columns to the \'Find Patients\' table, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Open the nh_searchFields table in the selected global database and find the jsonName of the field you wish to turn on</li>\r\n	<li>Write a global&nbsp;patch which inserts this field into the nh_serSearchFields for the service who needs this field:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nINSERT INTO nh_serSearchFields (`fieldId`, `ser_id`, `order`) VALUES (\r\n&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;(SELECT fieldId FROM nh_searchFields WHERE jsonName=\'JSON_NAME_HERE\' LIMIT 1),&amp;nbsp;\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; SERVICE_ID_HERE,\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; 100\r\n);</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-22 12:20:03','2016-09-22 12:20:03',NULL),(276,65,33,'Getting PAF Log Data','How to get Postcode Address Finder log data from the servers','<p>To extract PAF log data, run the following query on both the Demo paf_log database and the live paf_log database:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nSELECT&amp;nbsp;\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; paf_log.serviceId,\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; services.serviceName,\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; substring(UPPER(paf_log.postcode), 1, 2) as pcArea,\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; count(*)&amp;nbsp;\r\nFROM paf_log&amp;nbsp;\r\nLEFT JOIN services ON services.serviceId = paf_log.serviceId&amp;nbsp;\r\nWHERE paf_log.date &amp;gt; \'FROM_DATE_HERE\'&amp;nbsp;\r\nAND paf_log.date &amp;lt; \'TO_DATE_HERE\'\r\nGROUP BY paf_log.serviceId, substring(paf_log.postcode,1,2)\r\nORDER BY services.serviceName, pcArea</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-22 12:25:09','2016-09-22 12:25:09',NULL),(277,65,33,'Getting PAF Log Data','How to get a count of postcodes looked up by services from the Postcode Address Finder log','<p>To extract a&nbsp;count of postcodes looked up by services using the PAF, run the following query on both the Demo paf_log database and the live paf_log database:</p>\r\n\r\n<pre>\r\nSELECT&amp;nbsp;\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; paf_log.serviceId,\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; services.serviceName,\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; substring(UPPER(paf_log.postcode), 1, 2) as pcArea,\r\n&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; count(*)&amp;nbsp;\r\nFROM paf_log&amp;nbsp;\r\nLEFT JOIN services ON services.serviceId = paf_log.serviceId&amp;nbsp;\r\nWHERE paf_log.date &amp;gt; \'FROM_DATE_HERE\'&amp;nbsp;\r\nAND paf_log.date &amp;lt; \'TO_DATE_HERE\'\r\nGROUP BY paf_log.serviceId, substring(paf_log.postcode,1,2)\r\nORDER BY services.serviceName, pcArea</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-22 12:26:14','2016-09-22 12:26:14',NULL),(278,66,32,'Add Field to Group Sessions','How to add a field to group sessions for a service','<p>To start with, you need to know whether the field you need to add to group session exists in the nh_fields table.&nbsp;If the field&nbsp;<strong>does not</strong>&nbsp;exist, you need to write a patch which adds it to the nh_fields table and arrange for it to be deployed. You cannot add it to group sessions until this has been done.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>To add an&nbsp;<strong>existing</strong>&nbsp;field to group sessions, follow these steps:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Write a patch which adds the field to the nh_fieldsSer table. Check the notes for help replacing the placeholders in this query:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>\r\n		<pre>\r\nINSERT INTO nh_fieldsSer table (fieldId, priority, type, course_order, ser_id, live) VALUES (FIELD_ID_HERE, PRIORITY_HERE, TYPE_HERE, COURSE_ORDER_HERE, SERVICE_ID_HERE, 1);</pre>\r\n		</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;Add the fieldId into nh_fieldsSer table, set priority, course_order = \'position in which the field appears on the front end\'.</li>\r\n	<li>Add the field to the groups template.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Notes:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Replace the following placeholders in the query above with:</p>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>FIELD_ID_HERE: id of the field you want to add to group sessions</li>\r\n	<li>PRIORITY_HERE:&nbsp;<strong>1</strong> if always&nbsp;mandatory, <strong>2</strong> if manadtory unless \'allow less than minimum dataset\' is ticked, <strong>3</strong> if always optional or <strong>4</strong> if always mandatory for MDS</li>\r\n	<li>TYPE_HERE:&nbsp;<strong>0</strong>&nbsp;for not dataset specific,&nbsp;<strong>1</strong>&nbsp;for IAPT dataset,&nbsp;<strong>2</strong>&nbsp;for Employment&nbsp;dataset, <strong>4</strong>&nbsp;for CYP dataset</li>\r\n	<li>COURSE_ORDER_HERE:&nbsp;the number of the position that the field appears on the iaptus front end</li>\r\n	<li>SERVICE_ID_HERE: id of the service you want to add the field for</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-22 12:39:46','2016-09-22 12:39:46',NULL),(279,68,17,'Core iaptus Tables','Created\r\n73 months ago by Erica Bradbury\r\nLast Updated\r\n72 months ago by Erica Bradbury','<h3>nh_session:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Clinical contacts are stored in the nh_session table. Clinical contacts can be saved as \'incomplete contacts\', which allows a therapist to come back and complete them at a later date. They&nbsp;can also be marked as deleted which prevents them from&nbsp;appearing on the front end of iaptus.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are 2 columns relevant to incomplete and deleted contacts: the \'live\' column and the \'temp\' column for which the entries don\'t work exactly as you might expect - see the table below.<