SET stage_shotcut = \'yes\'\r\nWHERE ser_id = 101\r\nAND `id`=STAGE_ID_HERE);</pre>\r\n',1,1,'2016-09-22 13:21:45','2016-09-22 13:21:45',NULL),(291,80,11,'Accessing SMS XML Log','How to access SMS information using the iaptus SMS log feed','<p>As all IAPTUs SMS messages have their statuses routed through the iaptus.co.uk server. We can use this to get a cross service count of messages and filter by service and/or date. This information is available through a web api at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://beta-crm.mayden.co.uk/library/1769/%20http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/xmlfeed.php\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/xmlfeed.php</a>&nbsp;which requires various parameters passed in. You can see the available options and test it using &nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/test.php?secretknock=mayden\">http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/test.php?secretknock=mayden</a>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Current options include filtering by service and date and how the information should be grouped and&nbsp;displayed. The following are examples of this&nbsp;(copied from &nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/test.php?secretknock=mayden\">http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/test.php?secretknock=mayden</a>):</p>\r\n\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/xmlfeed.php?type=sms\" target=\"_blank\">No Parametes</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/xmlfeed.php?type=sms&amp;IQLU6C0U4QCHLZEEC56XGKMEQ6OOXWFO1N4N9P872TRH1GB2X590EHX698RP=LAJG72RA2CA51HQIZRI0MN4YE5ZNPSYBXSE0IBLGIEW31HW8VT2B96L1DTHK\" target=\"_blank\">No extra parameters</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/xmlfeed.php?type=sms&amp;idinloop=1&amp;IQLU6C0U4QCHLZEEC56XGKMEQ6OOXWFO1N4N9P872TRH1GB2X590EHX698RP=LAJG72RA2CA51HQIZRI0MN4YE5ZNPSYBXSE0IBLGIEW31HW8VT2B96L1DTHK\" target=\"_blank\">idInLoop-</a><br />\r\n<a href=\"http://www.iaptus.co.uk/public/xmlfeed.php?type=sms&amp;byMonth=1&amp;IQLU6C0U4QCHLZEEC56XGKMEQ6OOXWFO1N4N9P872TRH1GB2X590EHX698RP=LAJG72RA2CA51HQIZRI0MN4YE5ZNPSYBXSE0I